title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix butter, sugar and bananas; add beaten eggs.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Add walnuts last.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Cook at 350° for 50-55 minutes.
This is mixed by hand.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas with a fork.
Stir in other ingredients and bake in a greased loaf pan for an hour at 325°.

title: fiesta tamale pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, cook and stir ground beef, pork sausage, onion and garlic until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomatoes, corn, olives and seasonings.
Heat to boiling.
Pour into ungreased dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch or a 2-quart casserole.
Mix cornmeal, milk and eggs.
Pour over meat mixture.
Sprinkle cheese and bake 50 to 60 minutes or until golden brown.

title: vanilla balls
directions: I didn't have potatoes, so I substituted rice.

title: hot artichoke spread
directions: In a bowl, combine first 5 ingredients. Spread into a 1-quart baking dish or pie plate. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until top is lightly browned. Sprinkle with tomatoes and onions. Serve with crackers or pita bread.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix Dream Whip according to package instructions. Add mayonnaise and cream cheese. Mix well and fold in fruit and marshmallows. Refrigerate.

title: goonie birds
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until fluffy. Gradually add sugar; continue beating.
Add salt, 2 or 3 drops of food coloring and the peppermint extract.
Beat until stiff.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Cover cookie sheet with tinfoil; do not grease.
Place by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet; put in oven. Keep heat on for about 5 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Let stand in closed oven several hours or overnight.

title: frosty orange punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and it's cold and ready to serve.

title: firey cajun shrimp
directions: Wash shrimp thoroughly.
Combine first eight ingredients.
Put shrimp in large Pyrex dish.
Pour all of sauce over shrimp.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes.
Stir twice.
Butter French bread and brown.
Sauce can be used as a dip for the bread.

title: sunday beef roast
directions: Season roast with salt and pepper and place in slow cooker. Add onion and mushrooms. Add soup. Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours or high for 6 hours.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together well all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons half full into hot grease and cook about 5 minutes.

title: meatball soup
directions: In large cooking pot, prepare mixed vegetables.
When tender, drain and set aside the cooking
water from vegetables.
To vegetables add noodle soup, tomato soup and beef bouillon dissolved in vegetable water.
Add meatballs as they brown.
After browning meatballs, pour off fat.
Add 1/2 to 1 cup water to pan and scrape meat pieces. Add to soup.
More vegetable water can be added, depending on how thick you like it.
Freeze leftovers.

title: peterson potatoes
directions: Parboil potatoes and broccoli.
Cut both into bite-sized pieces.
Cut onion into large chunks.
Place 1/2 of these ingredients in casserole and cover with 1/2 of olive oil.
Add remaining 1/2 of vegetables, cover with remaining oil and season liberally.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Butter bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form pan generously. Sprinkle with cracker crumbs; shake pan to coat all sides.
Let excess crumbs remain on bottom.
Heat oven to 325°.
In large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese with mixer until fluffy.
Beat in sugar gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in flour, salt, pumpkin and spice.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes or until firm around sides, but soft in center.
Turn off heat.
Open oven door a crack; let cake cool in oven 30 minutes.
(Top of cake will have cracked during baking.)
Remove cake from oven.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Remove sides of pan.
Chill.
Before serving, top center with whipped cream.
Makes 10 servings.

title: helen potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Leave overnight.
Then bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice and milk together in double boiler one hour.
Add vanilla.
Beat lightly 2 whole eggs and 3 egg yolks and then beat in 1/2 cup sugar.
Add egg and sugar mixture to rice.
Stir until a little thick.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish or loaf pan.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, water and Karo until spins a thread.
Beat egg whites and vanilla until peaks form.
Pour hot ingredients into egg whites.
Beat until smooth and stands in a peak.
Stir in pecans just before spooning on wax paper.

title: coconut raisin treasure cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees. In bowl, mix graham cracker crumbs, flour and baking powder. In mixer bowl, beat sweetened condensed milk and margarine until smooth. Add crumb mixture; mix well. Stir in raisins, coconut and nuts. Drop by tablespoons on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake for 9 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool 2 to 3 minutes; remove from cookie sheet. Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with onion in boiling water (salted) about 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Stir in carrot.
Fold in drained squash and onion.
Melt butter or margarine; toss with stuffing mix.

title: steak roll-ups
directions: Pound steak to 1/3 inch thickness.
Cut into six pieces. Combine the onion, butter, bread crumbs, celery, parsley flakes, salt, poultry seasoning and pepper.
Place 1/3 cup on each piece of steak; roll up and fasten with a toothpick; roll in flour.
In a large skillet, brown roll-ups in oil.
Combine soup, water and browning sauce if desired; pour over roll-ups.
Cover and simmer for 2 hours or until meat is tender, turning occasionally.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: creamy onion dip
directions: Blend sour cream and onion soup mix. Stir in Blue cheese and nuts.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: cheesy crescents
directions: Open roll according to package directions.
Cut cheese to fit into rolls.
Roll up and generously sprinkle top of rolls with sesame seed.
Bake according to package directions.
Makes 8 rolls.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, put 1/2 the dressing. Add chicken and then add the rest of the dressing. Mix soup and milk. Pour over casserole. Top with butter and cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cooked through.

title: "whipped cream" frosting
directions: Blend cornstarch with 1/4 cup of the sugar and salt in small heavy pan.
Mix in milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick and smooth.
Cool to room temperature.
Beat remaining 3/4 cup sugar with the room temperature butter and vanilla and add cornstarch mixture.
Beat on high speed until fluffy and whipped. Refrigerate cake in hot weather.
Great on any cake, especially chocolate.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Put all together. Cook as long as you want.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into balls about 1-inch in diameter.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes.
May be frozen before baking.
Place on cookie sheet. Freeze until firm.
Place in plastic bags.
Freeze.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix milk and soup well.
Add all vegetables.
Keep part of cheese to put on top.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and cover. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until macaroni is done.
Uncover last 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and let sit for 15 minutes before serving.

title: fresh vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.

title: unicorn chicken salad
directions: Mix all together.
Makes approximately 12 sandwiches.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cold water and fruit.
Pour into 3-quart dish.
Cover with marshmallows.
Refrigerate and allow to set-up.
Mix eggs, flour, sugar and pineapple juice together in pan and cook until thick.
Cool.

title: yellow cake
directions: Mix flour, baking
powder
and	salt;
set
aside.
Add sugar slowly to shortening, beating well.
Beat in egg smooth, then add other egg
and beat well.
Add half the flour, mixing half of the milk and
the
vanilla, then add rest of the flour and milk.
Mix well.
Bake
at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes until cake springs back when lightly touched near center.

title: moon cake
directions: Mix 1 cup water and oleo; bring to a boil.
Add flour all at once and stir rapidly until mixture forms a ball.
Cool a little while.

title: fruit pizza
directions: On pizza pan, press cookie dough flat.
Bake 10 minutes or until brown.
Whip cream cheese and whipped topping; spread on cooled crust.
Top with fruit in circular pattern.

title: salmon packets
directions: Cut potatoes into 1/3-inch thick slices.
Cut 4 pieces of foil, each about 8 inches square.
Dip potato slices in the butter, then place equal portions on pieces of foil.
Top each with 2 tablespoons of green onion.
With a sharp knife, cut strips of salmon away from the skin in pieces 3 to 4 inches long, 1 1/2 inches wide and 1/2 inch thick.
Place equal portion over potatoes.
Sprinkle each with salt and 1/4 teaspoon of dill. Drizzle with remaining butter.
Pull up corners of foil and twist to seal.
Bake in a 325° oven for 20 to 25 minutes until fish turns pink.
Serve with lemon wedges.
Serves 4.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: brazil nut cake
directions: Mix fruit and nuts together. Sift dry ingredients together and add to fruit mixture.
Stir in eggs and flavorings.

title: one dish meal
directions: Divide meat in half.
Pat into 2 large patties on foil.
Cut onions, carrots and potatoes in bite size pieces on top of meat. Sprinkle salt and pepper on top to season.
Add margarine on top of vegetables.
Fold the aluminum foil up around meat and vegetables.
Place in shallow pan and cook in oven 1 hour at 400°. Serves 2.

title: coco's cake(pancakes)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl; stir until blended. Cook and enjoy.

title: graham cracker foamy
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender container.
Blend until smooth and frothy.

title: easy dill pickles
directions: In bottom of pint jar, put dill seed and cloves garlic, sliced. Add small cucumbers or large ones quartered lengthwise.
Fill jar with syrup made of vinegar, water, sugar and pickling salt boiled until sugar is dissolved.
Put on lids and set on stove in pan of hot water.
Heat 5 minutes after water comes to boil.
Remove jars and tighten bands.
Save extra syrup for next batch.
A larger amount of syrup may be made ahead and stored in cupboard.

title: quick taco platter
directions: Cook beef until brown.
Drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and seasoning.
Simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cover a platter with chips; top with lettuce.
Layer with beef mixture, tomato, onion and cheese.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: meringues
directions: Beat all ingredients together but add sugar 1/4 at a time. Bake at night in a 275° oven for 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Turn oven off and leave door closed overnight.
Bake on brown paper bag. Make 9 meringues.
Keep well wrapped.
Better baked on a dry day.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 350° in loaf pan.

title: low-fat nachos and cheese snack
directions: Put chips on a cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with both cheeses and put in a 350° oven until cheese is melted.
Take out and dip in salsa.

title: frosted carrot cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; set aside.
Combine brown sugar and next 7 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Stir in dry ingredients and beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until well blended.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham crackers and 1 stick margarine and pat on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat 2 sticks margarine, eggs and powdered sugar and spread on top.
Drain and spread pineapple on top.
Slice bananas and spread on top.
Frost with whipping cream.
Decorate with cherries, nuts and coconut.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Cut in 12 to 15 squares.

title: super breakfast pizza
directions: Cook bacon; drain and crumble.
Separate rolls into 8 triangles.
Place in an ungreased pizza pan to form a crust. Sprinkle bacon over crust evenly, then sprinkle hash brown potatoes over bacon.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese evenly over that. In a bowl, beat the eggs, milk, salt and pepper; pour over crust. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Bake in a 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let set a few minutes.
Slice.
Serves 6.

title: rainy day texas barbecue
directions: Wipe meat with damp cloth.
Rub with 1/2 of the Crisco and all the crushed chili; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
In a 1-quart saucepan, boil water.
Add remaining Crisco and all butter; allow to melt.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Place meat in medium-size mixing bowl.
Pour over top and let stand at room temperature for 4 hours or refrigerate, covered, for 2 days, turning from time to time.
Preheat broiler and place as far from heat as possible.
Boil 15 minutes, turn and baste with liquid smoke and marinade, rubbing over surface, and continue to broil for 15 minutes per side for a total of 1 hour, repeating marinade and liquid smoke.
Baste with sauce, slice and serve.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Simmer finely chopped onion.
Brown ground meat and pour off all fat.
In bowl, combine eggs, mayo, milk and cheese.
Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Pour over ground meat and onions.
Mix thoroughly again.
Spoon into pastry shell and bake at 350° until cheese is melted and pie is set.
Before baking, sprinkle garlic powder over top of pie.

title: italian green beans
directions: Place green beans and water in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add onions, salt and pepper.
Stir.
Dot with butter.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Garnish with onion slices, if desired.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and drain.
Add all ingredients, except 1/2 the cheese.
Mix and bake at 350° until bubbly.
Sprinkle the rest of the cheese on top and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Combine butter, salt, thyme, chopped chives or parsley and marjoram. Shape into a roll, about 8 inches. Wrap in waxed paper. Freeze for 20 minutes plus. Flatten chicken with rolling pin between sheets of waxed paper until thin. Cut butter in 4 to 6 pieces, depending on how many meat pieces you have. Put one on each piece. Roll up tightly, enclosing butter. Fasten with toothpicks. Beat 1 egg and water together. Dip meat into it and roll in 1/2 cup wheat germ.
Bake in shallow pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 400°.

title: shrimp louisiana casserole
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in butter until tender-crisp.
Add shrimp and continue cooking 3 minutes longer. Stir in soup, rice, parsley, lemon juice and seasonings.
Add bread, which has been soaked in milk; mix well.
Spoon into buttered, shallow 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Beat together the cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Line a muffin pan with cupcake papers. Place 1 teaspoon of the crumbled cookies in each cup. Fill each cup 1/2 to 3/4 full. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. When cool top each cake with canned pie filling. (Cherry is good, and raspberry is better!) Makes about 2 dozen.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat together shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla until creamy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and add raisins and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: sweet and sour - salad dressing
directions: Whisk vinegar and sugar, then add Miracle Whip until well mixed.
Taste.
Add more sugar or vinegar to your taste.
Makes 2 cups.

title: great grandma's recipe for soft molasses cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
In separate bowl, combine shortening, sugar, extract, molasses and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Add hot water last.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Blend in blender for a minute or so.
Store in a covered jar in refrigerator.
Will keep for 2 weeks or more.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Place layer of crushed potato chips in bottom of greased baking dish.
Add layer of sliced zucchini, onion and green pepper.
Sprinkle with grated cheese, salt and pepper, pimentos and paprika and dot with butter.
Repeat layers.
Pour milk over all.
Bake, covered, at 350°.

title: salsa
directions: Place vegetables in a large kettle and add rest of the ingredients.
Put mixed pickle spices in a cheesecloth bag before adding.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 30 to 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Ladle into jars and seal.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.

title: cheese spread
directions: Heat Velveeta cheese and milk; stir until cheese is melted. Cool.
Combine pimentos, then add beaten egg, sugar and vinegar. Add to the cheese mixture.
Heat until well mixed and cool.
Add Miracle Whip.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Place sugar, brown sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla in bowl. Attach bowl and beater.
Turn to Speed 2 and mix for 30 seconds. Stop and scrape bowl.
Turn to Speed 4 and beat for 30 seconds. Sift flour, salt and baking soda together.
Gradually add flour mixture to sugar mixture on Stir Speed, about 2 minutes.
Increase to Speed 2 and beat for 30 seconds.
Add chocolate chips on Stir Speed and mix for 15 seconds.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Yield:
3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: chicken croquettes(serves 4)
directions: Boil potatoes; peel and mash.
Chop onion and fry in oil.
Add chopped chicken and green peas and continue to fry.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix with mashed potatoes and add mayonnaise. Shape into patties (makes 12 to 15).
Dip into flour, then beaten egg and then in bread crumbs.
Deep fry.

title: easy macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in baking dish; pour macaroni into melted butter. Stir until butter coats macaroni.
Slice cheese.
Cut each slice in fourths.
Add salt, pepper, cheese and cold milk to macaroni. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not stir while baking.
This comes out of the oven golden brown and creamy.

title: aunt elvira's little hot biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients thoroughly, then cut in lard.
Add milk and lemon juice.
Mix until mixture forms a soft dough.
Roll out on a well floured board to 1/2-inch thickness.
Fold in half and roll twice.
Cut with small biscuit cutter and bake in hot oven.

title: mama's ole tyme banana pudding
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt.	Stir in milk.
Cook over low heat stirring constantly until thickened.	Cook 15 minutes more stirring occasionally.
Beat egg yolks and gradually stir into hot mixture.
Return to heat.
Cook 5 minutes stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Line bottom of casserole with vanilla wafers.
Top with a layer of sliced bananas.
Continue another layer of wafers and bananas.

title: egg casserole
directions: Butter bread slices and cut into cubes.
Put into a buttered casserole (use 9 x 9-inch pan).
Sprinkle with dry mustard, salt and onion.

title: easy brownies
directions: Melt margarine in microwave.
Stir well after adding each ingredient.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 18 to 20 minutes. Do not overbake.
Frost.

title: corn muffin casserole
directions: Mix and bake all ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: carameled waffles
directions: In a medium bowl, beat eggs lightly.
Stir in milk and oil. Add corn muffin mix, onion powder, thyme and black pepper.
Blend until batter is slightly lumpy.

title: sandy's hot dog sauce
directions: Brown hamburg with onions.
Drain grease.
Add water and spices.
Cook until water is gone.
This can be put in freezer bags and frozen until ready to use.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to butter mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Divide batter in half.
Stir spices, raisins and pecans into one part.
Pour plain mixture into 2 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Pour spice batter into 2 (9-inch) greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pans on wire rack 10 minutes. Remove from pans and cool completely on wire rack.
Prick cake layers at 1-inch intervals with toothpick.
Spread frosting on layers, starting with spice layers, ending with plain layers. Cover top and sides with frosting.

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage. Add onions and water chestnuts. Cook 5 minutes. Cook rice according to package directions and mix with sausage mixture. Serve warm.

title: chicken divan
directions: Line bottom of 8 x 12-inch baking dish with broccoli or asparagus.
Layer chicken over this.
Mix salad dressing with cream of chicken.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over this.
Cover entire dish with dressing mix.
Dot with butter, cover and bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Put marshmallows and milk in pan and melt.
Crumble crackers; put all other ingredients in and mix.
Put on wax paper; flatten out to about 1 inch.
Store in refrigerator.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together; chill overnight.
Serve with sliced pineapple, bananas, apples, grapes and strawberries for dipping or may be used over fresh fruits as a dessert.

title: sandra's taco dip
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Spread onto 9-inch round, approximately 1-inch thick.
Top with some or all of the following, chopped: cheese, lettuce, tomatoes and black olives.

title: danish holiday butter cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually and continue beating until fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients. Gradually add to creamed mixture and mix until thoroughly blended. Shape dough into 2 balls and chill overnight.
Roll and cut into desired shapes.
Bake in a 400° oven until lightly browned on greased cookie sheet.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add raisins, walnuts, melted butter, and applesauce.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 9 x 2 or 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 2 pan. Bake at 350° for 45-50 minutes.
Cool.
Spread with icing made with confectioners sugar and butter.
Sprinkle with shredded orange rind. Decorate with whole walnut meats.

title: broccoli-chicken casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli until tender.
Cook onion until tender and drain.
Melt 1/2 cup margarine and blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk; cool until thick.
Blend in cream cheese. Place vegetables in 1 1/2-quart casserole with cubed chicken.
Add sauce and lightly toss.
Top with cheese.
Melt remaining butter and toss with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into small balls. Place on ungreased baking sheet and cook at 375° until golden brown.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
On waxed paper, coat breasts with flour.
In a 12-inch skillet on medium-high heat in hot vegetable oil, cook chicken until lightly browned on all sides.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Do not use mixer!
Add eggs and milk.
Mix well with a fork. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes.
Your favorite flavoring may be added.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and Crisco, then add sifted flour, spices, salt, soda, vanilla and water.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: "ergolavous" - almond logs
directions: Beat butter until creamy; add sugar gradually, mixing well. Beat in egg yolks; stir in almond extract and flour and mix well. Shape into 1-inch logs, using about 1 teaspoon dough for each log. Dip in slightly beaten egg whites; roll in slivered almonds. Place on cookie sheet; bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until light golden brown.
Yield:
about 40 to 50 logs.

title: roast meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs slightly with a fork.
Stir in milk, oats, salt, m.s.g., savory leaves, pepper and parsley; set aside. In hot skillet, saute onion in butter until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add to egg mixture, along with ground chuck.
Mix well until combined.
Line a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with waxed paper. Turn meat mixture into pan, packing down well.
Refrigerate, covered, at least 2 hours.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Carefully turn out into shallow baking pan, keeping original shape.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, make glaze.

title: macadamia nut cream pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine 1 cup milk, 1/4 cup sugar and 1/4 cup of nuts, salt and vanilla; scald.
Blend the remaining 1/3 cup of milk with egg and cornstarch.
Thoroughly stir some of the hot mixture into egg mixture; return all to saucepan.
Cook 5 minutes more, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Cool 1 hour.
Beat 2 egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually add the remaining 1/2 cup sugar, beating until stiff.
Fold carefully into cooled mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill.
Top with sweetened whipped cream and remaining 1/4 cup nuts.

title: lo-cal vegetable dip
directions: Blend all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: ants on a log
directions: Clean and pat dry several stalks of celery. Spread peanut butter inside celery. Cut each celery stalk into thirds. Place raisins on peanut butter. Enjoy this healthy, nutritious and fun treat.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together and shape into a loaf. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: creamy corn
directions: Combine cream cheese, milk, margarine and onion salt in small saucepan.
Cook over low heat until cream cheese and margarine are melted.
Stir in drained corn.
Cook until heated thoroughly, stirring constantly.

title: quick hollandaise sauce
directions: Do not let eggs cook or they will curdle.

title: cheese rounds
directions: Grate cheese and add enough mayo to make a paste consistency. Add mustard, Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Spread over slices of Pepperidge Farm party rye and broil until browned, about 2 minutes.
The spread can be made days ahead and refrigerated. Makes 2 loaves.

title: angel biscuit
directions: Combine dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Stir in yeast and buttermilk.
Roll out like regular biscuits.
Bake on middle rack at 450°.
May be refrigerated for as long as a week.

title: haddock fillets
directions: Pre-heat heat oven to 350°.
Pour tomato sauce mixed with oil over fish.
Onions and celery are cut into sauce.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: tomato preserves
directions: Skin tomatoes by scalding them in boiling water.
Mix sugars, water, lemon juice and rind.
Boil for 15 minutes or until syrup is thick.
Add tomatoes and cook until tomatoes are clear (220°), about 50 minutes; skim.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Add cornbread mix to other ingredients one box at a time. (Mixture will be thick.)
Put in well-greased glass dish.
Cook at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Let stand about 30 minutes to set.

title: venison chops on grill
directions: Mix oil, pepper, garlic salt, parsley, paprika, wine and lemon juice together and rub each chop with mixture.
Place chops in a flat dish and pour marinade over them.
Chill for about 4 hours. When you are ready to cook the chops, wipe each chop with a damp cloth to remove excess marinade.
Rub both sides of chops with olive oil.
Wrap each chop with a slice of bacon and secure with a toothpick.
Grill on an open grill for about 15 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll into balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Bake for 8 minutes in 375° oven.
Press chocolate kiss on each cookie.
Bake for 2 to 5 more minutes.

title: harvest casserole
directions: Frozen vegetables should be thawed just enough to separate. Start heating oven to 375°.
Combine chuck, onion, tomatoes, Worcestershire and salt.
Pat into 1-inch layer in a 3-quart casserole.
On top, place in layers the potatoes, flour, corn, limas, then green pepper.
Bake, covered, 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Gently stir and sprinkle with cheese; bake, uncovered, 30 minutes longer or until vegetables are tender.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix vegetables together in a shallow dish.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil.
Cook 5 minutes.
Pour over vegetables. Cover and marinate for 24 hours in refrigerator.
Drain and serve.

title: best cheese enchilada
directions: Mix onion and cheese together.
Mix oil and tomato sauce together.
Pour half sauce into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put a couple of tablespoons cheese mixture on corn tortilla and roll up. Place in baking dish.
Continue until all cheese mixture is finished.
Pour remaining sauce on rolled up tortillas.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: no bake peanut butter crunchies
directions: In heavy saucepan bring sugar and corn syrup to a rolling boil; remove from heat.
Add vanilla and salt.
Mix in peanut butter. In a separate bowl, mash corn flakes slightly.
Add peanut butter mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper and cool.

title: hobo beans
directions: Brown meat with onion; drain off fat.
Fry bacon and cut into small strips; drain off fat.
Combine meats and add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ham bake
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix broccoli, soups, 1 cup milk, the ham and onion powder in ungreased baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Mix baking mix and milk.
Pour evenly over soup mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Bake 30 minutes until golden brown.
Let stand at least 5 minutes.

title: creole sauce
directions: Cook onions and green pepper in butter until just tender.
Add tomato sauce and mushrooms.
Add salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Mix together the chicken, soup, milk, onion, Parmesan cheese, egg and cottage cheese.
Layer noodles, chicken mixture and cheese (ending with cheese as last layer).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 1/2 hour before serving.

title: coconut layer cake
directions: Sift first four ingredients into mixing bowl.
Drop in shortening.
Add flavoring, 2/3 of milk.
Beat 2 minutes or 300 strokes.
Scrape bowl and spoon often, add rest of milk and egg yolks and beat 2 minutes longer.
Pour into 2 (8-inch) pans 1 1/2 inches deep which have been lined on bottom with wax paper.
Bake in oven at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cool on wire rack 10 to 15 minutes before removing from pan and removing paper.
Frost with 7 Minute Frosting and cover top and sides with coconut.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine flour, cocoa, sugar and salt, adding milk gradually; cook in double boiler until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour small amount of mixture over egg yolks, stirring vigorously. Return to double boiler.
Add butter and cook 2 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla.
Cool and pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: chocolate cool whip pie
directions: Melt Hershey bar in microwave oven.
Fold into Cool Whip. Pour into pie shell.
Freeze until ready to serve. Thaw for 1 hour before serving, enjoy.

title: sheila's apple bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 2 (8 1/2 x 5 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch) loaf pans.
Stir eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla in medium bowl, well mixed.
Combine flour, baking soda and cinnamon on wax paper.
Stir into liquids until evenly mixed.
Stir in apples and walnuts.
Divide between 2 pans.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition until no egg is seen.
Add vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add jam, nuts and buttermilk.
Bake in 3 oiled and floured pans or a 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, or until done.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Arrange all ingredients in layers in the order given in a 2 1/2-quart covered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: carrot pudding
directions: Boil parsnips until almost tender; drain.
In a baking dish, melt butter or bacon drippings with enough brown sugar to form a syrup.
Place parsnips in this; season with salt and pepper.
Bake slowly until a golden brown.

title: baked mushrooms
directions: In a medium skillet, melt butter and saute onions until golden.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, beat eggs, then mix in crumbs, milk, cream, salt and pepper until crumbs absorb liquid. Blend in mushrooms and onions.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes until golden and set.

title: hungry jack beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Stir in next five ingredients and heat until bubbly.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Cut biscuits in half to form 20 half circles.
Place cut side down around edge of casserole.
Sprinkle around edge of casserole with cheese.
Bake at 375° until the biscuits are golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: jello and ice cream pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water, stir in ice cream.
Chill until very thick.
Fold in strawberries.
Pour into crust and chill until firm.

title: ham glaze
directions: Choose one of the three liquids (vinegar, wine or prune juice), and add to other ingredients.
Mix all ingredients together and add to ham before baking.
Use cloves and pineapple slices if desired.

title: baked apple
directions: Place cored apple in a shallow baking dish.
Pour soda and lemon juice over apple.
Sprinkle with sugar substitute and cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until apple is done.

title: corn chowder
directions: Heat oil.
Saute onion until soft.
Stir in flour.
Add corn. Gradually stir in milk.
Continue to stir until thick.
Add sugar, salt, white pepper, thyme and cream or evaporated milk.
Blend well.
Serve hot.

title: new ranger cookies
directions: Mix sugars, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Dough will be stiff.
Drop teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on ungreased sheet.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes.
Cool before removing.

title: ham delights
directions: Split Pepperidge Farm party rolls.
Spread mixture of first 5 ingredients on top and bottom of rolls.
Add sliced ham and cheese.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°.

title: aunt lee's garlic cheese grits
directions: Cook grits according to package.
While hot, stir in butter and cut up garlic cheese roll.
Let cool.
Add milk to eggs and stir into grits mixture. Pour into greased 2 quart casserole. Sprinkle top with grated cheese.
Bake in 300° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Drop from teaspoon on non-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 5 to 10 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Pour into baked shell.
Top with meringue.

title: cavacar de caldar
directions: You mix the flour with the oil and then you add the eggs, one by one, while you keep on mixing it.
You butter the molds and you let it cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: meatballs
directions: Place meat in a bowl and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Make into about 10 meatballs.
Brown in hot oil and then add to sauce.

title: cathedral window fruit salad
directions: Mix together in order specified.
It's better if made night before.

title: tossed salad with pine nuts in dill-garlic dressing
directions: Remove bottom core (about an inch or more) from each head of romaine and discard any outer leaves that are very dark green or heavy.
Wash lettuce thoroughly and tear into bite-size bits.
(At this point you can spin salad dry or wrap in clean kitchen towel and store in refrigerator until ready to serve.)

title: chinese shrimp and rice
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Saute onion, shrimp and rice until shrimp are pink.
Remove from heat; stir in eggs.
Bring broth, mushrooms with liquid, peas and soy sauce to a boil.
Stir in rice mixture; cover.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into casserole dish.
Mix topping and pour over potato mixture.

title: oatmeal cinnamon chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Beat butter, brown sugar and granulated sugar in bowl until buttery.
Add eggs, vanilla and beat well.
Combine flour and baking soda.
Add to butter mixture, beating well.
Stir in oats, cinnamon chips and raisins.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop by heaping teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: tuna salad filling
directions: Stir together all ingredients until well mixed.
Makes enough for 3 or 4 sandwiches.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Combine raisins, nuts, chopped broccoli, bacon, chestnuts and onion; toss well.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables.
Better if marinated several hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: lemon delights
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine lemon cake mix, Cool Whip and egg in large mixer bowl; mix well.
Form into small balls, using hands roll in confectioners sugar.
Place onto baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into balls the size of a small walnut.
Place on cookie sheets.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.
Makes about 60 cookies.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Saute garlic in margarine.
Add chicken broth.
Bring to a boil.
Add tortellini; reduce heat.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, spinach and basil.
Simmer 2 to 3 minutes; salt and pepper to taste.
May sprinkle with Parmesan cheese as served if desired.

title: stephanie's cinnamon rolls
directions: In small bowl combine water, yeast and sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Set aside.
In large bowl make pudding mix according to package directions.
Add butter, eggs and salt; mix well.
Add the yeast mixture; blend.
Gradually add flour and knead until smooth and the dough is no longer sticky.
Add sprinkles of flour until the dough is soft and silky feeling, but no longer sticky. Place in very large greased bowl.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk (about 1 hour).

title: vegetarian split pea soup
directions: Cook onion and garlic in oil until softened.
Put peas (split) and 7 cups water in large pot and add onion and garlic.
Bring to a boil slowly and simmer, covered, for about 45 minutes or until peas are very tender.
Cool slightly.
Blend in blender in small portions until fairly smooth.
Return to pot and add potatoes, carrots, celery and salt and pepper to taste.
When vegetables are tender; add frozen peas which have been thawed.
Cook for another 10 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and nutmeg.
Set aside. Beat butter, sugar and egg.
Beat in sour cream and vanilla. Gradually add flour mixture.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate overnight.

title: oven fried onion rings
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Coat 2 large baking sheets with the cooking spray.
Peel and slice the onions 1/2-inch thick.
In a pie plate, toss the bread crumbs, parsley, pepper and salt.
In a shallow dish, whisk the eggs until foamy.
Dip each onion ring first into the eggs, then into the bread crumbs.
Arrange in a single layer on the baking sheets.
Coat the onion rings lightly with the cooking spray.
Bake, turning 2 or 3 times, for 25 minutes or until crispy.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve lime Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water. Stir in 2 cups cold water.
Pour in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until partially set. Drain pineapple, reserving 1 cup juice.

title: quick & moist cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients (make sure its soupy) and pour into well greased iron skillet. Bake at 450° for 30-45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: three bean soup
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Fry bacon; drain and crumble.
Add to beans, tomato sauce, whole tomatoes and picante sauce. Slow-cook several hours.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Top with toasted almonds or Chinese noodles.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°. Serves 12.

title: farmer's breakfast
directions: Fry bacon and break into pieces.
Reserve 3 tablespoons drippings; add pepper, onions and potatoes.
Cook on medium heat for 5 minutes, until potatoes are brown.
Sprinkle with cheese. Melt.
Scramble eggs.
Add bacon, salt and pepper.
Mix together.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Put bacon drippings in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan; dust with corn meal and brown in oven.
Mix all other ingredients with corn bread mixture; pour over bacon drippings and corn meal.
Cook about 1 hour or until done.

title: barbecue biscuits
directions: In bowl, combine all ingredients except biscuit mix.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in biscuit mix to make dough soft.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: angel food cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugars until creamy; add egg.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix in sugar and egg mixture; add coconut and vanilla.
Roll in small balls (the size of a walnut).
Dip tops of balls into water, then in colored sugar.
Press them out on ungreased cookie sheet using fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not overcook!
Remove with egg turner and let cool.

title: belle fowler's coconut pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add flour alternately with the eggs, ending with flour.
Add flavoring.
Pour into greased tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Invert onto cake plate.
Loosen cake, leaving cake pan on top to cool.
This will create a crust on cake.

title: doctor bird cake
directions: Optional:
Sprinkle a few chopped nuts in buttered pan before adding batter for a crunchy topping; no icing needed.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Press hamburger meat firmly in baking dish.
Pour soup over hamburger meat.
Place Tater Tots over soup.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fresh fruit ice cream
directions: Chill all ingredients.
Add to bucket and process.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar, then add eggs one at a time.
Add coloring and cocoa.
Sift flour and salt together, then add buttermilk a little at a time with flour.
After mixture is mixed, sprinkle soda on top and mix good, then add vinegar and mix real good.

title: veal marsala
directions: Pound veal.
Combine flour, salt and white pepper.
Dredge veal in flour mixture and dust off excess.
Heat in pan 1 ounce of the butter and 1 ounce of oil; saute veal until brown on both sides.
Remove from pan to warm platter.
To pan, add 1 ounce of the butter, sweet scallions, onion and mushrooms.
Deglaze pan with Marsala.
Reduce by 1/3.
Whisk in 2 ounces of butter.
Pour over the veal and serve.

title: dilly rolls
directions: Warm large bowl by allowing hot water to stand in it a few minutes.
Pour in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add yeast and stir with wooden spoon until dissolved.
Warm cheese slightly in double boiler over warm water.
Add to yeast mixture, then beat in sugar, dill seed, onion flakes, soda, salt and butter.
Add egg, then stir in flour until it is all moistened.
With rather sticky dough still in the bowl, knead until it appears slightly smooth.
You may add some flour, but none is preferable.
Grease top of dough.

title: amazing peanut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except coconut and nuts.
Blend on low
speed	for 3 minutes.	Stir in nuts and coconut, pour into a 9-inch greased pie pan.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: country captain chicken
directions: Flour and salt chicken.
Brown in oil.
Remove.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic.
Cook 3 minutes. Blend in tomato sauce, water, seasonings and currants. Mix well.
Replace chicken.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Garnish with almonds.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix Cool Whip and softened cream cheese.
Slice cake.

title: stuffed brussels sprouts(hors d'oeuvres)
directions: Blot cooked sprouts dry with paper towel.
Hollow out the top of each, saving these leaves.
Cream the cheese with your choice of dressing and add nuts.
Stuff each hollow and set upon a plate (sometimes hard to stand up) and sprinkle top with paprika. Excellent Christmas choice as it is green and red.
Puree the remaining leaves with nuts and cheese.
Serve on crackers.

title: vanilla cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs together.
Add flour and flavor. Drop on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake in a 350° oven for 12 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Pour this mixture over bean mixture.
Let stand 24 hours to marinate.

title: macaroni and cheese with chicken and broccoli
directions: Combine one box of cooked macaroni and cheese with ham and broccoli.
Serves 3.
Enjoy.

title: garden casserole
directions: Cook
celery
in 1/2 cup water about 15 minutes; drain. Combine
all ingredients in casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Top
with
tablespoon Parmesan cheese and bake 5 more minutes.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Put 1 1/2 cans sauce and soup mix in Dutch oven with 2 (8 ounce) cans water.
Simmer, covered, 10 minutes.
Mix remaining 1/2 can sauce, thyme, garlic and parsley with hamburger.
Roll in balls and drop gently in sauce and simmer, stirring gently, uncovered, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: oatmeal chocolate chips
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, cream the shortening, brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Add eggs and mix thoroughly. Combine the baking soda, salt and flour and add to creamed mixture.
Knead until thoroughly combined.
Add oatmeal and chocolate bits; continue to knead until well mixed. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes. Yields 1 dozen.

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in margarine for 10 minutes. Stir in next 6 ingredients.
Combine eggs and cheese.
Add to zucchini mixture. Separate crescent rolls into 8 triangles.
Place in ungreased 10-inch pie pan.
Press over bottom and up sides to form crust.
Spread crust with mustard.
Pour zucchini mixture into crust.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: chicken wings
directions: Discard wing tip; cut remaining wing in two pieces.
Dip chicken wing in melted butter.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese, salt and garlic powder in a plastic bag.
Shake wings in crumb mixture. Place chicken on greased 15 x 10-inch baking sheet and bake in preheated oven at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: dump cake
directions: Use 13 x 9-inch pan.
Dump in cherry pie filling; spread. Cover with pineapple.
Sprinkle cake mix over fruit.
You may add coconut and/or chopped pecans at this time.
Cover top with oleo. Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: christmas glow punch
directions: In large punch bowl, combine punch, pineapple juice and cranberry juice cocktail.
Slowly stir club soda.
Add ice cubes. Garnish with lemon or lime slices, if desired.
Makes 5 quarts or 38 (4 ounce) servings.

title: pickled beets
directions: Reheat cooked beets.
Add spices.
Let simmer for 15 minutes.

title: jello popcorn balls
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to boil; remove from heat.
Add jello; stir until dissolved.
Pour over popped corn; stir well.
Make into balls.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix everything together.
Place in cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: whole wheat walnut sticks
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Rub fat in as for pie crust.
Pour water, gradually mixing into stiff dough.
Knead very thoroughly on board.
Press out with hands on board until about 1/2 inch thick and cut 1/2 x 3-inch strips or roll dough into sticks and bake 1/2 hour in moderate oven (325° to 375°).
Roll or turn once or twice during baking.

title: meringue shells
directions: Cover a cookie sheet with brown paper.
Draw 8 (3-inch) circles on paper; leave 1-inch between each.
In a small mixing bowl, beat egg whites, vanilla and cream of tartar until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, beating on high speed until stiff peaks form.
Pipe or spoon onto brown paper.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Turn off oven and let shells dry with door closed for at least 1 hour.
Peel off brown paper.

title: rice jello
directions: Put 1/2 c. rice (not instant) into 3 cups water.
Boil slowly until rice is done.
Add Jello, any flavor (I like orange) right in the rice hot water and all, mix well.
Add sugar, crushed pineapple, and salt.
Put in refrigerator in bowl and let set until just about hardened, then stir in Cool Whip.

title: copper pennies
directions: Peel carrots, cover with water and cook until tender.
Drain while hot.
Layer with other vegetables.
Combine soup, vinegar, oil, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, salt and pepper.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over layer of vegetables. Marinate overnight.
Great to keep in refrigerator for snack. Serves 10 to 12.

title: chocolate applesauce cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt, spices and cocoa.
In a large mixing bowl combine oil and sugar.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in hot applesauce, blending thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients, blending well.
Stir in raisins and walnuts.
Turn batter into two well-greased 9-inch square pans.
Bake in hot (400°) oven for 15 minutes and then reduce oven to 375° and bake about 15 minutes longer.
Let stand in pan 5 minutes.
Remove from pans and complete cooling on racks.
Frost with Caramel Frosting.

title: chocolate peanut butter squares
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar, melted margarine and vanilla until well blended.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt the chocolate chips over low heat.
Pour and spread over mixture like frosting.
Let set before cutting.

title: watermelon fire and ice salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Makes 3 cups.

title: grace's chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until meat comes off bone.
Let cool; then remove bone and skin.
Remove meat and cut up.
Grease casserole dish (or use Pam cooking spray).
Mix soups (uncooked) with chicken broth. Layer casserole dish in order:
meat, both soup/broth, onion, stuffing crumbs (lightly enough to cover), melted butter, poured over stuffing.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove foil last 5 minutes of baking, so top may brown. Serves 6 people.

title: grilled lemon chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Season with salt and pepper. Combine margarine, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until margarine melts; mix well.
Brush over chicken.
Place chicken on grill.
Add 3 presoaked hickory chips to coals.
Grill over low coals for 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender, turning and basting frequently.

title: cottage cheese pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook in lightly oiled skillet or griddle until lightly browned on both sides.
Top with applesauce and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Good source of protein, great for kids lunches.
No junk.

title: water whip pie crust(perfect every time)
directions: Put Crisco, boiling water and milk in a bowl. Tilt the bowl slightly and whip ingredients together with a fork until mixture looks like glossy mayonnaise.
Add flour and salt and mix again with fork until mixture cleans the bowl.
Work with hands into two balls of dough.
Roll out between lightly floured waxed paper. (You can use half now and freeze the other half in a plastic bag. Just thaw for several hours and then roll crust between sheets of waxed paper.)
Yield: double crust.

title: cherry salad
directions: Combine ingredients in order listed.
Mix well after each addition.

title: crumb crust
directions: Mix thoroughly and place on apples, patting lightly.
Makes enough for two pies.
Also good as a topping for homemade ice cream.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Mix and sift together flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add milk and butter; mix well.
Pour into medium sized shallow baking pan.
Pour 2 cups peaches on top of batter and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: creamettes
directions: Boil macaroni in salted water until almost done.
Rinse and drain.
In a casserole, place a layer of macaroni, a few pats of butter, some juice and some finely cut cheese.
Repeat with another layer.
Continue until all is finished.
Bake in a 350° oven until cheese and butter are melted, about 45 minutes.

title: big red cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
After cake cools, poke holes in cake.
Mix jello and Big Red.
Pour over cake.
Mix Cool Whip and pudding.
Spread over cake.

title: chocolate cake
directions: To make buttermilk, take one cup milk and add 1 tablespoon vinegar.
Let set while you start mixing the batter.
Stir occasionally.
Cream shortening or oil with sugar and cocoa.
Add eggs, stir well.
Add buttermilk, then flour, soda, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° until done.
Use 8 x 8-inch pan or whatever you have.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Cut beef into chunks or use stew beef.
Brown beef, if desired.
Put in deep baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan and heat to boiling stage.
Add to meat.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours, removing cover for last half hour.

title: walking pudding
directions: Mix instant pudding with milk in a bowl, according to package directions.
Pour into flat bottom ice cream cones.
Refrigerate until set.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: play dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients in heavy saucepan. Add oil, water and food coloring.* Cook 3 minutes or until mixture pulls away from sides of pan. Store in plastic bag, sealed.

title: onion twists
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix baking mix, milk, onion powder and oil.
Beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Gently smooth dough into ball on floured cloth covered board.
Knead 5 times.
Divide dough into 32 equal parts and roll each into pencil strips (12-inches long). Twist into pretzel shape on ungreased cookie sheet.
Brush all with egg wash; sprinkle with salt.
Bake 10 minutes until brown. Serves 32.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Butter baking dish.
Spread bread and alternate with grated cheese.
Pour over milk and egg mixture.
Store in refrigerator for one or two days.
Then bake 1 hour at 300° to 325°.
Serve with spinach souffle (frozen), spinach or broccoli.

title: kobi russ' no-bake cookies
directions: Combine the sugar, cocoa, butter and milk in a medium saucepan.
Cook on medium heat, stirring frequently.
Bring to a boil; let boil for 1 minute.
Turn off heat; add peanut butter, vanilla, oats and nuts (optional).
Mix together and drop with a tablespoon onto waxed paper or foil until set.

title: slimmer crab cakes
directions: Mix prepared mustard, salad dressing and egg together.
Add crab meat, seasonings, mustard, cracker meal and parsley.
Mix lightly so as not to break up the crab meat.
Form into cakes. Fry in small amount of oil until brown; turn and brown on other side.
Cakes may also be broiled.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate peanut buddy bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In a large bowl, beat peanut butter and butter until smooth, about 1 minute. Add sugar, eggs and vanilla extract; beat until creamy. Blend in flour and salt. Stir in one cup chocolate morsels. Spread in ungreased 13 x 9 baking pan.

title: sugar-free jello salad
directions: Mix jello using 2 cups boiling water, 1/2 cup cold water. When jello begins to set, add other ingredients.

title: pineapple jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in the boiling water.
Cool.
Drain pineapple (save juice).
Spread pineapple in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Layer with marshmallows, then layer of sliced bananas.
Pour cooled Jell-O over and refrigerate until firm.
Mix 1 cup pineapple juice, lemon juice, egg, cornstarch and butter.
Mix well.
Cook until thick.
Let cool.
Mix Dream Whip as directed on package.
Add to cooled custard.
Spread on Jell-O.
Top with chopped nuts.

title: egg rolls
directions: Will need 30 to 35 pieces of egg roll wrappers.
Combine first five ingredients in a bowl.
Add salt and pepper.
Then add egg and soy sauce.
Combine mixture thoroughly.

title: potato-leek chowder
directions: Separate and wash the leeks.
Slice them into 1/2-inch pieces. In a nonstick large saucepan, saute the potatoes and leeks in the butter or margarine for several minutes, stirring the vegetables to prevent browning.
Add the broth, pepper and salt.
Bring the chowder to a boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer chowder for 20 to 30 minutes or until tender.
Add the milk gradually; heat the chowder gently, but do not boil.
Stir in the parsley.
Serve chowder with a generous sprinkle of grated cheese.
If desired, puree in blender before adding milk.

title: stuffed vidalia onions
directions: Steam
Vidalia	onions	by
wrapping each one in a damp paper towel.
Microwave
at
Full
power	about 10 minutes or until tender.
Spoon
out inside pulp, leaving 3 outer layers of onion. You
should
have
a
circular opening.
Place in a casserole dish;
set	aside.	Combine
all
other ingredients except garnish.
Place
stuffing mixture equally into each of the steamed Vidalias.	Microwave
for	2 or 3 minutes at Full power
until well
heated.
Garnish each stuffed onion with 5 boiled
shrimp around top edge of onion.
Sprinkle center with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients with an electric mixer until well blended.
Bake in a greased cake pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
A toothpick inserted will come out dry when cake is done.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix in punch bowl or large container.
Use half of sherbet in each punch bowl mixture, as it makes it too full to use it all.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in margarine until tender. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well and simmer for 10 minutes. Good with hamburgers.

title: stuffed crabs(quick)
directions: Saute vegetables in butter and oil.
Add crab meat and bread crumbs; simmer for about 15 minutes, stirring often.
Cool and stir in eggs.
Stuff crab shells.
Sprinkle the tops with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with milk.
Add vanilla and prunes last.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peas and broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Combine mayo, vinegar and buttermilk.
Pour mayo mixture over vegetables and mix well. Chill at least 1 hour before serving.
Add peanuts before chilling, if desired.

title: pork chops and sage onions
directions: Coat chops with flour.
Brown in oil and margarine over low heat.
Turn and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Brown lightly on other side and remove from skillet.
Put onion in fat.
Toss to coat, then brown lightly.
Add 1 teaspoon salt and sage.
Add chops and water.
Reduce to simmer.
Cover tightly and cook slowly about 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together with hands and form one round cheese ball. Refrigerate.

title: microwave twice baked potato boats
directions: Arrange potatoes in a circular pattern on micro-type plate. Use cook cycle and cook 12 to 13 minutes or until tender, turning potatoes over once during cooking.
Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: oven meal
directions: Place ingredients in baking dish in order given.
Salt and pepper each layer.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pineapple coconut lemon pie
directions: Mix all of the above; pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 300°.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Blend in sugar and salt.
Coat pecans.
Melt butter on cookie sheet and pour nuts onto this.
Bake in 325° oven for about 45 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes at first and then about every 3 minutes.

title: bacon quiche biscuit cups
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 10 muffin cups.
In small bowl, beat cream cheese, milk and eggs on low speed until smooth.
Stir in Swiss cheese and onion; set aside.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Place 1 biscuit in each greased muffin cup; firmly press in bottom and up sides, forming 1/4-inch rim.
Place half of bacon in bottom of dough-lined muffin cups.
Spoon about 2 tablespoons cheese mixture over bacon in cups.
Bake for 21 to 26 minutes or until filling is set and edges of biscuits are golden brown.
Sprinkle each with the remaining bacon.
Lightly press into filling.
Remove from pan.
Makes 10 servings.

title: no fuss pumpkin bread
directions: In a 9 x 5-inch well-greased loaf pan, mix in first 8 ingredients with a whisk until all is moistened.
Stir in the raisins and nuts.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.
Run knife around rim to loosen bread, then remove.

title: honey butter spread
directions: In a sauce pan combine sugar, cream, and honey. Heat on medium high heat stirring until it comes to a boil.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix (add flour until thick) and bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: milley's newfie pie
directions: Beat egg whites, water, salt and sugar until ropey consistency.
Add vinegar and continue beating until thick. Cover Pyrex pie plate with waxed paper.
Pour mixture onto plate. Bake for 1 1/2 hours in 300° oven.
Remove from oven and turn upside-down on plate.
When cool, cover with whipped cream and strawberries.

title: scotch shortbreads
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the butter.
Gradually add the sugar, beating well.

Mix the flour, salt and baking powder together and add to the first mixture. Combine thoroughly. Roll out dough with a rolling pin until it is 1/4-inch thick, then cut into rectangles or any shape desired.
Put on ungreased cookie sheets; prick each cookie with a fork and bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until they turn lightly brown around the edges.

title: manicotti
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in pan; add spaghetti sauce.
Cook noodles and drain.
In bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, put slight layer of sauce, layer of noodles, carton of cottage cheese, package of Mozzarella cheese, 1 layer of sauce, layer of noodles and layer of sauce.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: roberta's white bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender or food processor; puree until smooth.
Let stand several hours to develop flavors.
Serve with corn chips.

title: sonny's pizza dough
directions: Put yeast in water; add salt and oil.
Add flour; knead until smooth.
Put in greased bowl; raise 1 hour.
Punch down; let rest 10 minutes.
Divide in half; roll out.
Makes 2 (16 inch) pizzas.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in a medium saucepan and bring to a rolling boil.
Boil, stirring constantly, until the mixture forms a soft ball when dropped into a cup of water.
Take off heat and add peanut butter; do not stir.
When peanut butter has melted, stir until the mixture thickens and begins to loose its gloss.
Pour into buttered cookie sheet.
Cool until firm.
Cut into small pieces.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: beef baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and bell pepper; drain.
Add other ingredients except pork and beans; simmer 15 minutes or until sauce thickens.
Add pork and beans.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: wash day peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a medium saucepan over medium heat, cook fruit until boiling.
Set aside.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream butter, cheese and sugar until smooth.
Beat in egg yolks.
Add vanilla and flour.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Remove from oven and press in chocolate kisses.

title: face paint
directions: Mix this small amount or multiply to make larger quantities. Muffins tins work well as both mixing bowl and artist pallette. This paint removes easily with cold cream.
This paint was used at the Kid's Circus Summer of 1993.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Fill paper muffin cups 2/3 full.
Cream sugar and cheese; beat in egg and salt.
Stir in chocolate pieces.
Drop one rounded teaspoonful of cheese mixture into each cupcake.
Bake as cake box directs for cupcakes.

title: fruit cream icebox pie
directions: Blend milk and lemon juice thoroughly; fold in drained fruits. Stir in Cool Whip; pour into crusts and chill 2 hours before serving.

title: chili dip
directions: Mix well and enjoy.

title: navajo fry bread
directions: Add yeast and water together; let stand.
Combine all other ingredients together. Add to yeast and water.
Let rise, then fry in hot grease.

title: bodin
directions: Boil first 6 ingredients until tender; grind.
Add remainder of ingredients; mix well.
Stuff in pork casings.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Save broth and cook spaghetti in it. Add melted oleo; stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook in 350° oven until bubbling hot.

title: bom boms
directions: Melt and mix margarine and peanut butter together (well).
Add powdered sugar and roll up into balls.
Cool for 30 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips and 1/2 stick paraffin and dip balls using a toothpick.
Better when chilled.

title: the big "b" crab cakes
directions: Combine gently.
Do not break lumps.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°. Then broil remaining 5 minutes.
Careful not to burn.

title: laura's no fat strawberry cake
directions: Set strawberries aside.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease and flour Pyrex 23 x 18 x 4-inch glass dish.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 4-cup container, mix sugar and syrup. Microwave 4 minutes at 100% power. Add peanuts. Stir until peanuts are coated. Microwave 4 minutes at 100% power. Add baking soda. Stir until light and foamy. Spread on cookie sheet. Let cool. Break in pieces.

title: gooseberry cheesecake
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar, gooseberries and water and cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until thick; let cool.

title: cola cake
directions: Blend sugar and flour in mixing bowl. In saucepan put Coke, oleo, cocoa, oil and marshmallows. Stir until mixture begins to boil and keep warm or until all the marshmallows are melted real well. Pour this mixture into the sugar and flour mixture and mix well.

title: beth's artichoke dip
directions: Place all ingredients in baking dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly. Serve with crackers or chips.

title: no-knead refrigerator rolls
directions: In
mixing
bowl,
dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt and
about	half
the
flour.
Beat thoroughly 2 minutes. Add
egg and
shortening.
Gradually
beat in remaining flour until smooth.
Cover
with damp cloth; place in refrigerator. Punch down occasionally as dough rises in refrigerator.
About 2 hours before
baking,
cut
off
amount
needed
and return remaining dough
to refrigerator.
Shape into rolls and place on greased baking sheet.
Cover.
Let	rise until light (1 1/2 to 2 hours). Heat oven to
400° (moderately hot).
Bake 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 4 dozen medium rolls.

title: herbed croutons
directions: Cut bread sticks into 1-inch pieces.
Mix dressing with butter and toss onto bread.
Bake in a 350° approximately 10 minutes until golden brown.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Mix milk and pudding mix according to package.
Add whipped topping and blend.
Pour into large covered glass dish and refrigerate.
(You may freeze if you like.) Makes 8 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: harvest apple pie
directions: Pare apples and slice thin in large bowl.
Combine the sugar, cornstarch, spices and salt; mix with apples.
Scatter the red hots over the mixture; dot with butter.
Put on top pastry; prick holes in top of the crust.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 15 minutes more.
Serve with ice cream or a wedge of Cheddar cheese.

title: cheese pepper muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 (2 1/2-inch) muffin cups real good.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and pepper in small bowl.
Mix egg, milk and oil until blended. Stir into flour mixture just until moistened.
Fold in 3/4 cup of the cheese.
Spoon into muffin cups and sprinkle remaining cheese over tops.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until light brown.
Let cool in pan and serve warm.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken well done, pick off bone and cut up in small pieces.
Cut apple in very small bits; cut celery in very small bits.
Chop pecans in small pieces.
Add mayonnaise; mix well. Serve cold with crackers.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, mustard, celery seed, salt and pepper; mix well.
Add potatoes, eggs, onions, celery and pickles.
Mix well and chill.

title: sole inge-lise(sole stuffed with shrimp)
directions: Salt and pepper each fillet to taste.
Sprinkle each with dill weed.
Spoon shrimp into approximately the middle of each fillet. Roll up each fillet and place in buttered shallow 2-quart casserole.
(Fasten fillets with toothpicks if necessary.)
Saute chopped onions in butter until limp.
Combine cream or milk with cornstarch.
Then add tomato paste or catsup and mustard.
Pour over fish.
At this point, the casserole may be refrigerated for later baking.
Return to room temperature before baking at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamy mustard dressing
directions: Mix mustard with the garlic, lemon juice and pepper in a bowl. Adjust to taste.
Stir in mayonnaise.

title: coconut pecan pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour, milk, baking powder and flavoring.
Mix well; stir in coconut and pecans.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand in pan about 25 minutes; turn out on rack.

title: golden cream potato-cheese soup
directions: Combine potatoes, water, carrots, celery, onion, parsley flakes, salt, pepper and bouillon cube.
Cover.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes or until veggies are tender.

title: angel buns
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water in medium bowl.
Mix in Bisquick and milk until dough forms.
Gently smooth into ball on flour dusted surface.
Knead 10 times.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick. Cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter dipped in flour.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Let rise in warm place about 30 minutes or until soft and puffed.
Bake in 400° oven for 6 to 8 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 9 to 11 buns.

title: parmesan noodles
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Melt butter and add milk and continue heating until hot.
Remove from heat; blend in remaining ingredients.
Toss with hot pasta.
Season with salt and pepper. (Makes 3 servings of 1 1/3 cups each.)

title: bluegrass salad
directions: Whisk together first 4 ingredients. Chill. Melt butter in skillet over medium heat and saut walnuts about 5 minutes or until light brown. Remove with a slotted spoon. Toss together lettuce, pears, asparagus and walnuts. Sprinkle with cheese and cranberries. Drizzle with dressing.

title: cream of chicken soup
directions: In a large saucepan, melt margarine or butter.
Stir in flour and dash of pepper.
Add chicken stock and cream or milk.
Cook, stirring, until bubbly; cook and stir for 1 minute more.
Stir in chicken; heat through.
If desired, garnish with parsley.
Makes 3 main dish servings.

title: christmas pudding
directions: Combine ingredients; fill tin cans (16 ounce) 2/3 full, lids on while steaming.
Steam 3 hours in steamer or large roasting pan half full of water.
Fills 4 cans.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Line ungreased 9 x 11-inch pan with graham crackers.
Mix pudding by box directions.
Add whipped topping to pudding.
Pour mixture over graham crackers.
Line with another layer of graham crackers. Pour chocolate frosting over top and chill for 4 to 6 hours.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Arrange chicken pieces in glass baking dish.
Sprinkle sparingly with butter-flavored salt.
Dissolve bouillon cube in 1 cup hot water; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with Season-All salt. Cover and microwave on High for 20 to 30 minutes or until chicken is tender, turning every 5 minutes.

title: spinach and artichoke dip
directions: Melt butter in saucepan on medium heat. Add onion and cook until soft.
Stir in artichokes, spinach, cream cheese, 3/4 cup Monterey Jack and Parmesan cheeses, sour cream and optional Tabasco. Stir until cheeses are melted and mixture is well blended.
Pour mixture into a 1-quart
casserole dish. Top with some of the extra cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Serve with crackers or corn chips.

title: dilled carrots
directions: Bring broth to a boil in large saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients except parsley.
Cover.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes or until carrots are crisp-tender, stirring occasionally.
Drain.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: french fried onions
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Beat together and add flour mixture until smooth. Slice onions 1/4-inch thick.
Dip in batter and let drip.
Fry at 375° until brown.
Serve.

title: sunday brunch casserole
directions: Place bread in greased 9 x 13 baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine milk, eggs, mustard, onion powder and pepper in medium bowl.
Pour evenly over the bread and cheese.
Sprinkle sausage and optional ingredients over top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Bake uncovered for 55-60 minutes.
Tent with foil if top begins to brown too quickly.

title: broiled crab meltaways
directions: Slice English muffins in half and cut each into quarters. Place on cookie sheet. Mix remaining ingredients in small bowl. Spread on muffins. Freeze at least 30 minutes. IMPORTANT STEP (May be kept frozen for 2 to 3 weeks). When ready to use, broil frozen crab meltaways until they puff up and are bubbly and slightly golden brown. Serve hot. Makes 48 meltaways.

title: parmesan appetizer loaf
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Stir in milk, sugar, salt, egg, 1/4 cup butter and 2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl.
Turn greased side up.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double, about 2 hours.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 12-cup Bundt pan.
Combine flour and salt in bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients except soda in large mixer bowl; beat at medium speed until light and fluffy, scraping sides occasionally, 5 minutes.
Reduce speed to low; add dry ingredients and soda, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.

title: yummy non-alcoholic punch*
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: banana punch
directions: Blend bananas with a little water in blender.
Add all ingredients.
Mix 2 cups of mixture with a 2 liter bottle of ginger ale.
You can freeze mixture until ready to use.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Mix juices.
Dissolve sugar in boiling water; let cool and then add to juice.
Serves 10.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch cake pan melt 1/2 stick margarine.
Sprinkle 1 cup coconut and 1 cup chopped pecans over margarine.
Mix cake as directed on box.
Pour over ingredients already in cake pan.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs and pour over apples.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil.
Mix together.
Spread in greased, oblong cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: sliced bake potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if skin is tough, otherwise scrub and rinse. Cut potatoes into thin slices, but not all the way through.
Use a handle of a spoon to prevent knife from cutting all the way.
Put potatoes in baking dish; fan them slightly.
Sprinkle with salt, drizzle with butter and sprinkle with herbs.
Bake at 425° for 50 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake another 10 to 15 minutes until lightly brown.
Check with fork.
You may use caraway seeds or cumin in place of herbs.

title: cucumber dill dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Stir remaining ingredients until well mixed. Cover and chill.

title: chocolate delites
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water; add condensed milk, coconut, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven 15 to 20 minutes. Remove cookies from sheet at once; place on wire rack to cool. Yields 3 dozen cookies.

title: amish cream pie
directions: In medium saucepan, stir together sugar, cornstarch and salt. Whisk in half and half and cook and stir over medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter, brown sugar and vanilla until butter melts.
Pour into baked pie shell and dust with cinnamon.

title: dip for fruit
directions: Have marshmallow cream at room temperature.
Beat all ingredients together until smooth.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: tina's famous potato salad
directions: Peel and quarter the potatoes and place in a 3-quart saucepan. Add enough water to cover and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat and simmer, uncovered, until the potatoes are tender, for about 20 minutes. Drain and let cool. Cut the potatoes into chunks or slices, according to your preference.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Split chilies; remove seeds.
Arrange chilies, Cheddar and Monterey Jack cheese in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper; pour over chilies.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven; top with salsa.
Bake 10 minutes longer. Serve at once.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat sweet potatoes with electric mixer until smooth (works best if potatoes are warm).
Add beaten eggs, sugar, salt and cinnamon and mix well.
Add milk and lemon extract.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into prepared pie shell.
Use a 9-inch deep-dish pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pineapple best cake
directions: Mix ingredients as listed.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: date snowballs
directions: Put everything, except Rice Krispies and nuts, into a saucepan and cook over medium heat for 6 minutes, stirring occasionally. Put the 2 cups of Rice Krispies in a bowl and mix in the 3/4 cup chopped walnuts.
Pour date mixture over.
Cool until you can handle (not cold).
Butter your hands and roll mixture into small balls, then roll in coconut.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding, pineapple and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.

title: whole wheat rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water containing molasses.
Let set while you prepare the other ingredients.
Add oil and salt to yeast mixture.
Gradually add flours into yeast mixture to make a soft dough.
Turn out on floured surface and knead approximately 200 times until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl; grease top and cover.
Let rise until doubled, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down, cover and let rise 10 minutes.
Shape into rolls and place on greased baking sheet.
Grease top, cover and let rise until doubled, 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until nicely browned.
