Makes 3 dozen.

title: coconut-pineapple pie
directions: Beat margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add to remaining ingredients and pour into two 8-inch pie shells.
Cook at 400° for 15 minutes, then turn heat down to 350° and cook for another 20 to 25 minutes or until brown and set.
Let cool.

title: slush punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in bowl with boiling water.
Mix warm water and sugar together.
Bring to a boil.
Add dissolved Jell-O to the sugar and water mixture.
Let cool.
Add lemon and pineapple juice to jello mixture.
Mix well.
Put in 2 large containers.
Freeze. When ready to use, remove from freezer 4 to 5 hours ahead of time so it may thaw.
When it gets slushy, pour 7-Up over it and enjoy. Makes 2 large punch bowls.

title: hot-n-spicy popcorn
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Spoon popcorn on jelly roll pan. Combine butter and hot sauce.
Pour over corn.
Toss to coat well. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into pastry lined pie shell. Dot with 1 1/2 tablespoons butter.
Cover with top crust which has slits.
Bake until lightly browned at 425° (hot oven) for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Mix cornflakes and add 1/4 cup melted butter.
Sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: white chocolate crunch
directions: Coarsely chop chocolate in food processor.
Combine chocolate and shortening in microwave-safe dish.
Cook at 50% (Medium) power for 6 minutes until melted smooth.
Stir at 2 minute intervals. Combine chocolate with remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Let cool completely; store in airtight container.
Yields approximately 5 dozen.

title: baby carrot cake("try this cake-it is delicious")
directions: Mix eggs well.
Add oil and sugar, then add flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Add baby foods and mix well.
Bake in a well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° until toothpick comes out clean (approximately 35 minutes).

title: boston cream pie
directions: Early in day:
Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease one 9-inch round cake pan.
In large bowl, with mixer at low speed, beat first 8 ingredients just until mixed.
Increase speed to high; beat two minutes.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Prepare Creamy Custard Filling.

title: lemon-apple cake with lemon sauce
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch square cake pan.
Combine apples, cinnamon and nutmeg in pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over apples.
Pour melted margarine evenly over the dry mix.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Melt margarine in a saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients except oats.
Boil for 1 minute.
Add oats; stir real good.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: buttermilk cornbread
directions: Heat iron skillet with bacon drippings in 425° oven.
Mix ingredients.
Pour heated drippings in mixture.
Bake approx. 15-17 minutes.

title: frozen fruit cup
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar; chop cherries.
Add pineapple, pecans and cherries to cream cheese.
Fold in whipped topping and oranges.
Line muffin cups with paper cups; spoon mixture into cups.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash and slice cucumbers.
Peel and slice onions.
Combine all other ingredients and bring to boil.
Add cucumbers and onions and bring to a boil.
Cook 2 minutes over low heat.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.
Do not cook longer than 2 minutes or slices will be "mushy" tasting.

title: coconut philly fudge balls
directions: Gradually add sugar to softened cream cheese.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in vanilla and salt.
Shape into balls and roll in coconut.

title: cola barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion, ginger, garlic, and saut for 3 minutes or until tender.
Stir in cola, bring to a boil.
Stir in ketchup and remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: stolen pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt margarine and chocolate.
Add sugar.
Add flour.
Blend in beaten eggs and other ingredients, then pour into greased pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool before serving.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Beat eggs and sour cream.
Blend in oil, sugar and corn and corn meal.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick and easy german chocolate cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Add can of frosting and pour into greased and floured Bundt pan (spray with Pam).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes (probably will take longer, about 50 minutes).
Drizzle with frosting made of milk and powdered sugar. Can add sparkles.

title: plain cake
directions: Cream butter until soft.
Add the flavoring and the finely granulated sugar, stirring briskly until the mixture is light and fluffy.
Continue creaming and add slowly the well-beaten egg yolks.
Add the sifted dry ingredients and milk alternately, a little milk at a time.
Beat in the dry ingredients.
Stir in the milk.
The first and last addition should be the dry ingredients. Fold in the beaten egg whites last of all.
Pour the batter into a lightly greased pan.
Bake in a moderately hot oven at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes.
This batter may be baked in layer pan, or in muffin pans as cupcakes.

title: salsa(hot sauce)
directions: Peel and chop onions, chop chilies (seed removed). Peel and chop fresh tomatoes.
Add onions, chilies and other ingredients to chopped tomatoes.
Pack into hot jars and process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes or bring to a boil and pack into jars and seal. Process 5 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together well.
Add pumpkin, oil and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder, salt and spices.
Add to pumpkin mixture and beat.
Add pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 2 well-greased pans.

title: holiday pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large bowl, slightly beat eggs.
Stir in pumpkin pie mix.
Add evaporated milk, mix thoroughly.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes on bottom shelf of oven.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake 50 minutes more or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: philadelphia cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream oleo, cream cheese and sugar real well.
Add flour and eggs alternately.
Add salt and vanilla.
Pour in well-greased and floured tube pan.
Start in cold oven.
Bake 1 hour and 20 to 30 minutes in 325° oven.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Put oil in heavy skillet.
Fry shrimp for 1 minute.
Add eggs (beaten), mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Fry for 5 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Add rice and soy sauce.
Stir.
Add scallions.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Combine egg, broccoli, corn, onion, salt and pepper.
In small saucepan, melt butter; add stuffing mix.
Toss to coat.
Stir 3/4 cup of buttered stuffing mix into vegetable mixture.
Turn into 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with the remaining 1/4 stuffing mix. Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: candy apple fruit dip
directions: Mix and serve with apples.

title: peanut crunch cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cake mix, peanut butter and brown sugar on low speed until crumbly.
Set aside 1/2 cup.
Add water, eggs, and oil to remaining crumb mixture; blend on low until moistened.
Beat on high for 2 minutes.
Stir in 1/4 cup each chocolate and peanut butter chips.
Pour into a greased 13x9x2 inch baking pan.
Combine peanuts, reserved crumb mixture and the remaining chips; sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 - 45 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool completely.
Yield:
12 - 16 servings.

title: roasted pumpkin seeds(fun to do with children)
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Place seeds in colander and wash with warm water.
Mix salt, oil and seeds in a bowl.
Spread seeds on cookie sheet.
Bake for 30 minutes or until seeds are golden brown.
Stir seeds occasionally while baking.

title: scalloped corn
directions: In a bowl, combine first 8 ingredients.
Transfer to a greased shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 6 servings.

title: bologna stir-fry
directions: Chop bell pepper, onion and bologna. Drain jar of mushrooms. Put all ingredients into a nonstick frying pan.
Cook until done and serve.

title: dieter's dream dessert
directions: Add 2
cups
boiling
hot
water
to
gelatin
in large container.
Stir
until dissolved.
When thoroughly dissolved, add 2 cups
ice cold water and stir.
Refrigerate until it has gelled. Meantime,
open
cans
of fruit and drain thoroughly. Stir fruit into
gelatin
and add Cool Whip, stirring gently. If you
desire to
make
individual servings Cool Whip may be placed on top. Place strawberries on top.

title: barbecue chicken sandwiches
directions: Saute chicken and onion in butter.
Mix rest of ingredients together, then add the chicken and simmer one hour.
If dry, add 1/2 cup more water.
Crock-pot works great for this to heat through.

title: shrimp cocktail
directions: Combine all ingredients, except shrimp.
Chill thoroughly. Makes 1 cup cocktail sauce.

title: nut crackers
directions: Melt half of chocolate tidbits.
Cream shortening and sugar; add egg.
Continue beating and add vanilla and melted chocolate. Add milk and dry ingredients.
Mix in chocolate pieces and nuts. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for about 13 to 15 minutes.

title: cajun famous coleslaw
directions: Prepare the vegetables.
Mix all the ingredients together in a wooden or glass bowl.
Refrigerate for several hours.

title: old fashioned pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into two unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 400° for 1/2 hour.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Use a large cookie sheet with sides. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: dad's favorite snickerdoodles
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well. Mix in dry ingredients.
Form into balls and roll in cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: crustless egg custard
directions: Mix
together sugar and flour.	Add beaten eggs, melted butter,
milk
and vanilla.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Grease and flour pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken in water with bouillon cubes and salt until tender.
Remove from broth; debone and cube.
Set aside.
Cook macaroni in broth until tender.
Melt butter in saucepan and add flour; stir until smooth.
Add cheese and milk to flour mixture and cook until smooth.
Add this sauce to macaroni and mix together with soup, peas and pimentos.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch casserole.
Bake in 350° oven until piping hot.

title: german skillet beans
directions: Fry bacon; leave grease in pan.
Add onion and saute in bacon and grease.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer 10 minutes or until thick and heated through.

title: better than bob's barbecue sauce
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil and simmer until mixture thickens (about 10 to 15 minutes).
This is also better than bought.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine dry ingredients, then add egg and milk to consistency that can be dropped from spoon and fry in fish grease.
When adding either onion or both onion and green pepper, they can be put in a blender with egg and milk and chopped fine.

title: rice pudding
directions: Beat eggs and add enough water to make 2 cups.
Add egg mixture to hot pudding.
Also add vanilla.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Stir 1 cup of pecans, crushed pineapple, onion and salt into softened cheese.
Chill until firm; shape into a ball.
Roll in remaining pecans.
(May add 1/4 cup each of red and green pepper for holiday color.)

title: cauliflower dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Split a head of cauliflower and serve with dip.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Put nuts in bottom of pan, then coconut.
Mix cake as directed on box.
Pour cake over nuts and coconut.
Mix cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar together.
Spoon on top, but not near the sides of pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or a little longer.
Cool in pan about 45 minutes.
Put on cookie sheet and turn upside down.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Peel and boil potatoes; drain.
Add onion, salt and sour cream; whip.
Put in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Dot with butter or margarine and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: date-chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine dates, water and baking powder. Set aside to cool. Cream shortening, sugar and eggs and add to cooled date mixture. Add flour, salt, baking soda and vanilla. Pour into buttered and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with the 1/2 cup sugar, chips and nuts mixed together. Serve with whip cream. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: ham loaf
directions: The night before cooking, combine the milk and bread crumbs. Combine with the pork, ham and eggs; refrigerate overnight.
When ready to cook, combine the brown sugar, mustard, vinegar and water.
Separate the ham loaf into 2 loaves and pour the liquid over it.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 2 hours, basting the ham loaf well with the liquid about every 1/2 hour until done.

title: meatball scallop
directions: Mix ground beef, egg, bread crumbs, green pepper, mayonnaise and onion salt.
Shape mixture into 16 meatballs.

title: peaches and cream cake
directions: The Trick:
Mashed potatoes make it moist.

title: microwave streuseled apples
directions: In 8-inch square dish, place apples and 3/4 cup brown sugar. With pastry blender, mix flour, sugar, oats, butter or margarine and cinnamon until crumbly.
Sprinkle over top of apples. Microwave at High (No. 10) 9 to 12 minutes.
Let stand few minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken or turkey divan
directions: Cook broccoli until almost done.
Arrange in single layer in 9 x 13-inch pan (greased with butter).
Cover with layer of meat. Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over meat and broccoli.
Sprinkle with grated cheese, then sprinkle bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: apple cobbler number 1
directions: Put
apples in 14-inch Dutch oven in layers with pieces of butter, brown sugar and spices.
This should fill the pan. Cook over fire or coals until the apples are tender.
Mix cake mix
and Sprite
together; pour over apples.
Cook/bake until the top
of the cake is brown.
Serve hot or let set overnight for a good breakfast treat.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli in chicken broth.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, juice and cheese.
Drain broccoli and place in casserole dish. Place cut up chicken on top of broccoli.
Pour mayonnaise and cheese mixture over chicken.
Crush crackers into fine crumbs or use bread crumbs, crushed fine, and stir into butter.
Top casserole with crushed crumbs.
Bake at 350° until browned well.

title: monkey bread
directions: Put 2/3 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon into a plastic bag and set aside.
Take biscuits, shake in sugar mixture.
Put them in greased Bundt pan.
Take 1 cup sugar and margarine with 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bring to a boil and simmer for a few minutes. Add nuts to boiled mixture.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Turn on slate as soon as it comes out of the oven.

title: karo icing
directions: Beat all ingredients together until very stiff.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Use 2 or 3 teaspoons to 1 cup hot water.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together.
Bake in loaf pan at 325° until done.

title: veggie bars
directions: Press rolls into large cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Hidden Valley mix and spread over crust.
Sprinkle veggies on top, ending with cheese. Cool completely and cut into bars.

title: betty's barbecue sauce
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Let cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine chicken, vegetables, potatoes and soup.
Form crust in pie pan, then pour combined ingredients into pie shell.
Put on top crust.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Easy!!

title: neapolitan beef roll-up
directions: Pound steak until flattened.
Mix bread crumbs, Provolone cheese, pine nuts and garlic.
Spread evenly over 1/2 of round steak.
Flip other half over bread crumb mixture.
Place in nonstick baking dish.
Top with stewed tomatoes.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese and reserved bread crumbs over steak.
Drizzle with olive oil and lemon juice.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 6.
Approximate preparation time, 15 minutes. Cooking time, 35 minutes.

title: mamaw's cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water; set aside.
Scald milk, then add Crisco, sugar and salt; mix well.
Cool until lukewarm, then add 2 cups flour and eggs (well beaten).
Then add yeast and mix well.
Add 4 cups flour, mix well.
Knead lightly until smooth on board.
Place dough in a large covered pan and let rise until doubled.
Divide dough into 2 parts and knead lightly. Roll out thin and spread melted butter.
Sprinkle sugar, cinnamon and chopped nuts.
Roll dough.
Slice.
Place cut side down on greased pan to rise.
Bake at 375° until brown, then ice.
Enjoy!!

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in big bowl well.
Pour into rice cooker. Cook about 30 minutes or longer.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain, add salt and pepper.
Stir in mixed vegetables and soup.
Pour into 9 x 13 baking dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 to 30 minutes.
(Until bubbly.)

title: date loaf candy
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter to a boil.
Add dates and cook to soft boil stage.
Beat until it takes form and roll in damp cloth or wax paper.
Place in refrigerator or freezer.
Slice when ready to serve.

title: bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix milk and Bran; allow to set while mixing other items.
Mix first 5 items together.
In another bowl, mix egg and oil together.
Add bran mixture; mix.
Add dry items; mix briefly.
Put in muffin tins, filling each 2/3 full.
Bake 20 minutes.
Makes 12 to 14 muffins.
Freeze extras.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple (reserving 3 tablespoons juice).
Combine sugar and flour; stir in reserved pineapple juice.
Add cheese and pineapple chunks, mixing well.
Spoon mixture into a greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Combine melted butter and cracker crumbs, stirring well.
Sprinkle over pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, or until crumbs are lightly browned.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix hamburger, seasonings and 1/2 cup chopped onion all together, then form into oval shaped patties.
Put in pan, then broil for approximately 5 to 7 minutes on each side.
Open gravy and pour over patties.
Bake in oven for approximately 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: the smells of christmas
directions: Simmer over low heat or place pan on wood stove.
Add water often.

title: washington d. c. bean soup
directions: Brown ham lightly in 2 tablespoons butter.
Push to one side and cook the onion and celery until tender.
Mix in crock-pot: ham, onion, celery and all other ingredients.
Simmer several hours, stirring occasionally.

title: beef stroganoff(6 to 8 servings)
directions: Roll steak in 1/4 cup flour and salt.
Pan-fry onions, mushrooms and garlic in fat for 5 minutes.
Add steak and brown evenly.
Remove meat, onions and mushrooms from pan.
Add bouillon and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook until thickened.
Heat slowly until gravy simmers.
Add beef and vegetables and heat for a few minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve on hot rice, toast or noodles.

title: thunder cake
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Separate eggs; blend yolk in.
Beat the whites until stiff.
Fold them in.
Add cold water and tomato.
Sift together cake flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Mix dry mixture into creamy mixture.
Bake in 2 greased and floured 8 1/2-inch round pans at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Frost with chocolate butter frosting.
Top with strawberries (optional)

title: 7-up cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together except 7-Up. Add it last and beat well. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: slow cooker barbecue
directions: Combine roast and onions in slow cooker.
Combine cola and next 7 ingredients; reserve 1/2 cup in refrigerator.
Pour remaining mixture over roast and onions.
Cook, covered, on high for 6 hours or until meat is very tender.
Drain, cool and shred meat.
Keep warm.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix and form into ball.
Serve with snack crackers.

title: puff pancakes
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
In mixing bowl, combine flour, milk, eggs and touch of grated nutmeg.
Do not beat too much.
Scrape mixture into skillet.
Put in 425° oven for 15 or 20 minutes. Sprinkle xx sugar on top.
Squeeze 1/2 lemon over all.
Serve with marmalade or jams, lingonberries on top are best.

title: orange pineberry surprise
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add relish; mix well. Stir in pineapple, celery and nuts.
Pour into 6-cup mold; chill until firm.
Unmold on lettuce-lined plate.
Serve with mayonnaise dressing, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: garlic rosemary chicken
directions: Clean chicken; add salt and pepper to inside.
Add some rosemary, unpeeled garlic and 1 lemon, squeezed with rind.
In bottom of casserole, lay a bed of rosemary, garlic and squeezed lemon and rinds.
Place chicken on top.
Rub chicken with a little olive oil.
Sprinkle salt and pepper on chicken.
Lay rosemary and garlic and squeeze 1 lemon on top of chicken.
Cover; cook at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover 15 minutes before finished.
Carve thin slices.
Lay on a bed of watercress.
Pour juices over sliced chicken.

title: ham and onion spread
directions: Soften cream cheese; mix in ham, onions and mustard.
Chill. Serve with crackers.

title: yellow rice casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Mix other ingredients together first, then mix with rice.
Place in casserole dish and top with grated cheese. Cook in oven at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: flank steak with mustard-caper sauce
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon of the butter with the oil in a wide frying pan over medium-high heat.
Place meat in pan and cook, uncovered, until meat is browned on both sides but still pink in center when slashed (5 to 6 minutes total).

title: western baked beans
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: low-fat chicken parmesan
directions: Saute chicken breasts until done in just enough Canola oil to coat bottom of skillet.
Saute over medium heat.
Place chicken in casserole dish.
Pour spaghetti sauce over chicken.
Place lid on casserole dish and heat in oven at 325° until hot.
Remove lid; add cheese.
Replace lid until cheese melts.
Serve over spaghetti noodles.
Serves 4.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Heat asparagus to simmering and drain.
Place in a 2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Place slices of egg in a layer over asparagus.
Mix milk and Cheddar cheese soup until smooth and pour over asparagus and eggs, covering completely.

title: apple cake
directions: Add sugar gradually to oil.
Add eggs (one at a time), beat after each.
Measure flour with salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture.
Apples, vanilla, nuts and raisins next.
Bake in well-greased angel cake or Bundt cake pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: orange-glazed pork chops
directions: For glaze, in a small saucepan, stir together the sugar, cornstarch, orange peel, ginger root and red pepper.
Stir in orange juice and soy sauce.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.

title: southwestern hominy
directions: Coat nonstick skillet with cooking spray; place over medium heat until hot.
Add tomato and onion; saute until onion is tender. Stir in hominy and next 4 ingredients.
Spoon into a 2-quart baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Yields 6 servings.
Contains 66 calories and 1.4 grams fat.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together; place in flat casserole dish.
Lay chicken pieces on top.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper; brush with butter. Bake 2 1/2 to 3 hours in 275° oven.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Pour oil and sugar over apples.
Let set for 1 hour.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Add flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, allspice and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add walnuts.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes in tube pan at 325°.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach. Squeeze out water. Mix all remaining ingredients. Good served with chunks of sweet Hawaiian bread or whatever.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Chill.
Shape into balls or crescents.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cookies should be light on top and lightly browned on bottom.
Cool slightly and roll in additional powdered sugar.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add salt and taco seasoning, mix.
Drain well and cool.
In large bowl combine chopped lettuce, thinly sliced onion, black olives (drained), diced tomatoes, and hamburger mixtures.
Before serving add crumbled chips and Western dressing.

title: strawberry frost
directions: Whip for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth in blender.

title: dried apricot pie
directions: Soak apricots overnight in refrigerator.
Combine remaining ingredients and add apricots.
Cook all together in microwave oven for 10 minutes, then let cool a while before you put in the pie crust.
Put a few pieces of oleo on top, then cover with top crust.
Brush with milk and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: minnesota cucumbers
directions: Combine vegetables and mix with the celery seed. Dissolve sugar and salt in the vinegar.
Pour mixture over the vegetables. Cover and store in refrigerator.
Ready to eat after being in the refrigerator overnight. They will keep for about 2 weeks. Great for a family reunion!

title: butternut squash
directions: Peel squash; remove seeds.
Place squash in pot and cover with water.
Cook, covered with lid, until tender.
Drain and mash. Add other ingredients.
Stir well; pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° until firm.
Serves approximately 8.

title: snack bar coconut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Blend the cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in 2 cups of the coconut.
Pour the batter in the prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let cake cool in pan.

title: no bake fruitcake
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows.
Add remaining ingredients. Press into buttered tube or loaf pan.
Store in refrigerator.

title: key lime pie
directions: Crush crackers.
Combine with butter and press into a 9-inch pie plate.

title: taco dip
directions: Blend cream cheese with taco seasoning and smooth over plate. Top with chopped vegetables.
Pour taco sauce on top and ring with dollops of sour cream.
Serve with chips.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans, carrots, onions, soup and milk together. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes in a casserole dish.
Add onion rings to top and bake for 5 minutes.

title: fudge cookies
directions: Melt together butter, sugar and cocoa.
Mix eggs, flour and vanilla together.
Add cocoa mixture.
Add chopped nuts.
Bake in cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.
This recipe will serve 4 people.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter, syrup and salt in a saucepan. Bring to a boil; boil 5 minutes.
Beat in soda vigorously.
Stir in peanuts.
Place corn in a large shallow pan.
Pour sugar mixture over corn; stir.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Yield: 7 1/2 quarts.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Pour soup into casserole dish.
Add milk, little by little, stirring after each addition.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 1 hour or until macaroni is tender.
Serves 4.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Spread 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Spread frozen rhubarb in pan. Sprinkle Jell-O over rhubarb.
Sprinkle sugar over Jell-O, then spread dry cake mix over sugar.
Sprinkle water over cake mix. Pour melted oleo evenly over cake (more oleo may be used for a richer cake).

title: cranberry cake
directions: Beat first 6 ingredients 2 minutes, then stir in berries.
Put in a 9-inch pan and bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: summer jambalaya
directions: Cook sausage in Dutch oven until browned.
Remove sausage and discard drippings. Add ground beef, green pepper, green onions and garlic to Dutch oven. Cook until beef is browned. Drain. Add tomatoes, salt, pepper and sausage.
Cover.
Simmer 20 minutes. Add rice and water to meat mixture. Cover and cook 25 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Sift together flour and cinnamon and add to creamed mixture together with remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Drop from spoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake until brown in 350° oven.

title: easy cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill overnight.
If not able to chill overnight, reduce amount of sweetened condensed milk.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
In mixing bowl, mix 2 cups lukewarm water and the shortening.
Mix water and shortening a little while, then add the yeast.
Mix well, then add dry ingredients.
Let rise about twice its size, then roll out and cut out rolls.
Place on a greased pan; let rise again.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes, or until done.
Butter tops of rolls.

title: humbingers
directions: Brown sausage and beef.
Drain well and add Velveeta cheese while hot.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Spread on bread.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
These may be frozen before baked.

title: twinkie dessert
directions: Cut Twinkies lengthwise and lay in a 9 x 13-inch pan, cream side up. There will probably be one or two leftover.
Cover Twinkies with the butter pecan instant pudding, mixed as directed on the box. Cover the pudding with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle butter brickle bits over all.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
(Can be made ahead, the night before.)

title: oyster cracker mix
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add to oyster crackers.
Dribble oil until all is used.
Let set 8 to 10 hours and stir occasionally, about every 2 hours.

title: quick barbecued beef deli sandwiches
directions: Heat oil in skillet. Add onion and cook until tender. Add sugar and worcestershire sauce, soup, water and vinegar. Heat to boil, add beef and heat through. Serve on rolls.
Makes 6 sandwiches.

title: crazy cake 1
directions: Sift together dry ingredients into 8 x 8-inch pan (ungreased). Make three holes.
Mix together and add oil, vinegar and vanilla into holes.
Pour water over all and mix and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: congo squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter or shortening in saucepan. Stir in brown sugar. Remove from heat and cool for 10 minutes.

title: soft pretzels
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt, butter and egg.
Stir in 3 cups of flour; mix until smooth. Add enough additional flour to make a stiff dough.
Cover bowl tightly with foil; refrigerate for 2 to 24 hours.
Punch dough down and divide in half.
On a lightly floured surface, cut each half into 16 equal pieces.
Roll each piece into a 20-inch rope. Shape into the traditional pretzel shape and place on a greased baking sheet.
In a small bowl, combine egg yolk and water; brush over the pretzels.
Sprinkle with salt if desired.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 25 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown.
Yield:
32 pretzels.

title: ham pat
directions: Process ham until smooth.
Then add other ingredients.
Blend only until mixed.
Refrigerate overnight to mingle flavors.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Heat vinegar, sugar and butter in a saucepan.
Beat eggs and flour until smooth.
Pour in vinegar mixture until it starts to boil.
Stir until it thickens.
Chill.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add mayonnaise and mustard to cabbage when ready to serve.

title: lowbush cranberry juice
directions: Cook and cool cranberries.
Use 1/2 as much water by volume as lowbush berries.
Mix berries and water.
Boil for 5 minutes or until berries pop open.
Crush and strain mixture through jelly bag or large sieve to obtain clear juice.
To 1 quart Lowbush Cranberry Juice (see recipe), add 1 cup sugar and 1 cup water and boil for 5 minutes or until syrup consistency.
Add two cups of water, 1 cup orange juice (Tang may be substituted) and juice of 1 lemon. Chill.
Just before serving you may add ginger ale or can of 7-Up pop.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: In bottom of casserole dish or pan, pour pineapple with juice. Spread
pie
filling
over pineapple.
Spread dry cake mix over pie filling.
Cut
oleo
in
pats and place on top of cake mix. Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until brown on top.

title: christmas salad
directions: Add red Jell-O to boiling water; let stand to mold.
In saucepan, put milk, lime Jell-O, marshmallows and cream cheese. Melt.
Cool and add pineapple, pecans and Cool Whip.
Pour over red Jell-O and let stand overnight.

title: caramel apples
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, butter and 1/2 cup cream.
Cook over low heat until sugar dissolves; add mixture.
When it comes to a full boil, add rest of cream.
Cook to very hard boil stage (254°) without stirring.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Dip apples into syrup (work fast).
Roll in coarsely chopped nuts. Place upright on well-greased cookie sheet to cool.

title: goo goo candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips, add peanut butter.
Put marshmallows in large bowl, then pour peanut butter over marshmallows.
Stir until marshmallows are coated.
Place in buttered dish and cool.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: "mrs.  vera's" icebox cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Add sugar, butter and vanilla.
In another bowl, mix well the flour and chopped nuts. Make a hole in center of flour.
Add sugar, oleo and vanilla mixture.
Mix thoroughly.

title: white sauce
directions: Mix and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Thin with buttermilk.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Shape into balls.
May be baked in a 375° oven until brown or deep fried.

title: chicken alfredo
directions: Cut up chicken in pieces, cook in large skillet until almost done.
Then add bel pepper and onion.
Cook until chicken is done. In large bowl, mix chicken mixture and the other ingredients. Bake about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients.
Gradually add flour and baking soda.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 8 to 10 minutes, or until slightly brown around edges.

title: sausage balls
directions: Add cheese, sausage, Bisquick and seasoning into large bowl. Work together with hands until throughly mixed.
Roll into bite size balls.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: melanie's beef stroganoff
directions: Turn on your crock-pot on low. Pour in the 4 cans of soup. Put in the beef. Put on the lid. Go to work (6 to 8 hours). Come home. Turn the crock-pot off. Boil you some egg noodles. Put the sour cream in the crock-pot and stir. Now you're done. Put your noodles on the plates and put the beef gravy on top.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Add mayonnaise, catsup, pickle relish, sugar, as much American cheese as you want (about 4 to 6 slices shredded) and 1 or 2 boiled eggs, shredded.

title: cheesy celery snack
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stuff celery stalks or serve on crackers or bread.

title: chicken stuffing casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Fix Stove Top stuffing or your own stuffing. Shred chicken.
Add to 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Stir in cream of chicken soup, stuffing, mayonnaise and onion (already chopped). Stir up good.
Add 3 to 4 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar and stir.
Stir in Karo syrup. Add melted margarine and vanilla.
Put pecans in bottom of unbaked crust.
Pour filling over pecans and bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes.
(This does better in a crust that is not considered deep-dish.)

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed together.
Pour over cucumbers, onion and peppers.
Let stand a few minutes and put in jar.
Refrigerate.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Clean and slice mushrooms.
Make a roux with the butter and flour.
Cook roux for 2 minutes (do not blacken).
Add milk slowly, mixing well.
Add consomme; blend thoroughly.
Stir in mushrooms, heavy cream, salt and pepper.
Cook slowly for 10 minutes.
If soup is too thick, add warm milk.
Serves 4.

title: rice and chicken casserole
directions: Put 1 cup of rice on bottom of roaster, then put 1 package dry onion soup mix on top of rice.
Then put raw cut up chicken on top of that.
Season to taste.
Mix cream of chicken soup and 2 cans of water and pour over chicken.
Bake 1 hour with cover on and 1 hour with cover off to brown.
Bake at 350°.

title: seven-layer squares
directions: Place butter in a 9-inch square baking pan; bake at 325° until melted.
Remove from oven.
Layer graham cracker crumbs, coconut, chocolate morsels, butterscotch morsels and pecans with melted butter.
(Do not stir.)
Spread condensed milk evenly over top. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares and remove to wire rack to cool.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk and boil hard for 7 minutes.
Remove from heat and add chocolate morsels and butter.
Add vanilla and nuts; beat until smooth.
Pour into large greased container to cool (6 to 8 hours).
Cut into squares.
Store in container in a cool place.

title: white sauce
directions: Melt butter over low heat in a heavy saucepan.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Makes 1 cup of medium-thick sauce.
Best used in creamed and scalloped dishes.

title: aunt oletha's squash relish
directions: Grind the first 4 ingredients and add salt; let stand for 30 minutes, then drain off juice.
In a large pan, mix squash mixture with remaining seven ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes, but try not to boil.
Put into jars and seal.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and mix together well.
Pour batter into greased loaf pan.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pan, cool and slice.

title: fourteen karat cake
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon. Add sugar, oil and eggs.
Mix well, then add carrots, pineapple,
nuts and
raisins.
Mix
until	smooth	and pour into a greased and floured 10-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until cake
tests done
when	toothpick
is inserted.
Frost with a cream cheese frosting.
Keep refrigerated.

title: all-bran muffins
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.

title: sweet potato crest
directions: Mix all together and pour into buttered casserole.
Cook about 30 minutes at 350°.
Set aside.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain beans; add onion (sliced into thin rings) and green pepper (sliced into thin strips).
Mix sugar, vinegar and oil and stir all together.
Cover tightly and refrigerate 12 to 24 hours before serving.

title: microwave family meat loaf
directions: Combine sugar, tomato sauce and mustard.
Set aside.
Combine beef, onion, cracker crumbs, eggs, salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 cup of the tomato sauce mixture and stir until mixed good.
Place mixture in 8 cup micro-proof mold ring.
Pour rest of tomato sauce over meat.
Cook on High 18 to 20 minutes or until done.
Serves 6.

title: charlie's famous chicken and rice
directions: Bring chicken, bell pepper, celery and onion to a boil.
Boil for approximately 15 minutes or until done.
Pour contents through colander, reserving all of the stock.
Cut cooked chicken into quarters.
Return chicken and vegetables to pot.
Following rice instructions, use stock in place of water, adding an additional 1/4 cup of stock and cook as directed.
When done, add pimientos, if desired.
Best when served with either red or black beans (preferably red beans); recipe follows.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream butter until fluffy.
Add sugar to creamed butter and cream until light and fluffy.
Drop in 1 whole egg at a time while beating.
Stop beater and fold in flour.
Add vanilla.
Cook at 300° for 45 minutes.
Turn up to 325° for 15 minutes to brown.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: In saucepan, beat eggs.
Combine brown sugar and cornstarch. Add to eggs.
Then add milk (or canned milk).
Cook until the mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Then add oleo until melted.
Take off of the stove and add vanilla.
Let cool.
Pour into pie shell and refrigerate until cold.
Top with Cool Whip and nuts (nuts are optional).

title: zucchini pizza
directions: Mix together and put in oiled 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
After baking 25 minutes, spoon over some spaghetti sauce (enough to cover) and a little grated cheese.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Cook berries and mash them.
Cook until thick.
Put in an unbaked pie shell and place another unbaked pie shell on top of filling.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: alpha chapter's preference night dessert
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Bring to a boil and remove from fire.
Add Cocoa Krispies.
Spread in pan(s) and place in freezer 1 hour.
Allow ice cream to soften.
Spread on top of crust in pan and return to freezer until ready to serve.
Crush fresh candy canes on top.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add water to the two juices to make 4 cups.
Mix juices and jello together.
Save out 2 cups of juice and jello mixture and add pineapple and blueberries to remaining liquid.
Chill until firm.
Chill the remaining 2 cups of liquid until syrupy; add topping and nuts.
Pour this on top of first mixture and chill until firm.

title: oreo delight
directions: First Layer:
Place broken Oreo cookies in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: berry blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Add combined milk, butter, and egg; mix just until moistened.
Fold in blueberries.
Spoon into greased medium-sized muffin pan or paper-lined muffin cups, filling each cup 3/4 full.
Bake 18 - 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 5 minutes; remove from pan.

title: easy vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill at least 3 hours.

title: rhubarb jelly
directions: Cut up rhubarb into small pieces; cook until a hard boil for 5 minutes.
Measure rhubarb, sugar and Jell-O; mix well.
Bring to a hard boil, stirring constantly.

title: london broil
directions: Mix all ingredients except steak.
Brush top of steak with half of mixture.
Broil 4 inches from heat for 5 minutes.
Turn, brush other side and broil 3 to 5 minutes longer.
Slice thinly on diagonal and best served with Mushroom Sauce.
Serves 4 to 5. Excellent charcoaled.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Thaw spinach.
Butter a 9 1/2 x 5-inch baking pan or two smaller 7 1/2 x 3 1/2-inch pans.
Process bread into fine crumbs. Whisk eggs with milk, basil, salt and pepper.
Add spinach.
Turn mixture into baking pan.
Brush with ketchup and bake 30 minutes. Melt butter; baste loaf with butter and continue to bake, basting occasionally, until well browned, 30 to 40 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Drain blueberries and pineapple.
Save juice and add enough water to make 1 cup.
Add to jello.
Stir in blueberries and pineapple.
Pour into 2-quart container.
Combine sugar, sour cream, cream cheese and vanilla. Spread over jello and top with chopped nuts.

title: raisin nut cookie
directions: Soak raisins in warm water while mixing other ingredients. Cream the butter, brown sugar, white sugar and vanilla; add eggs and beat well.
Sift flour, soda and salt;
stir into first mixture.
Add oatmeal, raisins and nuts; chill.
Make in roll about 2 1/2-inches thick.
Bake at 360° for about 20 minutes.
Can freeze and bake as needed.

title: cheese olive puffs
directions: Drain olives on stuffed end for 1/2 day.
Mix cheese, flour, butter, salt, paprika and pepper real well.
Take approximately 1 teaspoon and wrap around an olive.
May be frozen ahead of time. Cook at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Place meat and mixture in large pan.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Mash with potato masher.
Serve on buns.
May be kept hot in crock-pot to serve.

title: three layer pie
directions: Mix the ingredients together until smooth and spread over the bottom of the cooled crust.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt oleo; mix other ingredients with oleo.
No cooking.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Stir boiling water into Jell-O in large bowl.
Be sure Jell-O is completely dissolved.
Stir in cold water.
Stir in ice cream until smooth.
Pour into serving bowl.
Refrigerate for 3 hours or until firm.
Garnish with fruits and top with Cool Whip.
Serves 8 people.

title: seafood croissants
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream and mayonnaise until smooth.
Add seafood, salt and Tabasco.
Spread seafood mixture on sliced croissants; top with Gruyere and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 8 minutes or until cheese melts.
Top with sliced avocado (lightly fan for good appeal).
Serve with fresh fruit.
Langostino can be substituted with crab or any seafood.

title: cherry pie
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups sugar and cream cheese together in mixing bowl. Then mix half of Cool Whip.
Pour half mix in a bowl.
You can put graham crackers on bottom or top and in middle, then put half cherry pie filling in middle, then repeat.
Pur the other half on top.

title: aunt lill's overnight salad
directions: Cook egg yolks, juice of 1 lemon, dry mustard and sugar in double boiler until thick.
Cool.
Cut pineapple and pears into small pieces.
Whip cream and mix with dressing.
Add cream to fruit.
Add cherries and marshmallows gently.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Bake cake in oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch as directed on package.
Cool.
Cut cake crosswise in half.
Reserve 1/2 for another dessert.
Cut remaining cake into 8 pieces; split each piece horizontally.
Arrange half the pieces in 2-quart glass serving bowl, cutting pieces to fit bowl.
Pour half the strawberries (with syrup) over cake; spread with 1 cup of the pudding.
Repeat with remaining cake pieces, strawberries and pudding.
Cover and chill at least 4 hours.
In chilled bowl, beat cream and sugar until stiff.
Spread over trifle.
Sprinkle with almonds and if desired, garnish with fresh strawberries.
Spoon into dessert dishes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: ricotta balls
directions: Mix together flour, Ricotta, milk and eggs until fully mixed and stiff.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Make a ball, drop into hot oil and brown to golden color.
Drain on brown paper to absorb grease. Shake confectioners sugar on Ricotta balls when cool.
Put in tin to keep fresh.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix together the oil, egg and sugar.
Add milk and salt; mix. Mix the rest of the dry ingredients together, then add to batter and mix well.
Stir blueberries in with a wooden spoon.

title: marilyn's good bread
directions: Combine water, shortening, sugar and salt in a small saucepan; cook, stirring constantly, until shortening melts.
Let cool to lukewarm (105° to 115°).
Dissolve yeast in mixture.
Add egg; mix well and stir in flour.
Spoon dough into greased muffin pans, filling half full.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, 1 hour or until doubled.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 14 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield:
15 rolls.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix the ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool completely.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together peanut butter, margarine and chocolate chips. Pour mixture over cereal, mixing together until well coated.
Put mixture into paper bag or plastic bag.
Add sugar and shake until mixture is well coated with powdered sugar.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain and add all other ingredients, except crackers and butter.
Put in casserole dish.
Crumble crackers on top.
Sprinkle butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: vivian's frito pie
directions: Layer with cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: mom's fruit salad
directions: Drain all juice, then use 1 can pineapple (chunk size).
Take the juice from pineapple and put in saucepan with sugar, flour and salt.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Beat egg yolk and add to sauce in pan; cook until thick.
Pour sauce over all the fruit. Add apples and oranges then chill until ready to serve.
Add bananas just before serving.
You can also add maraschino cherries or anything else that you like.

title: italian bread crumbs
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl. Makes 1 cup.

title: bread
directions: Mix 3/4 cup warm water and yeast together; mix in big round Tupperware bowl. Knead. Grease bowl; let rise until doubled in size. Punch down and let rise again. Put in loaf pans and let it rise again. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit pies
directions: Mix cherries and juice, pineapple, sugar, flour and red food coloring in saucepan.
Cook on medium heat until thick. Remove from stove; stir in Jell-O.
Let cool to room temperature.
Put in sliced bananas and nuts; mix well.
Empty into 2 crusts.
Store in refrigerator.

title: two grain lemon pilaf
directions: In medium saucepan, bring chicken broth to a boil.
Stir in celery, onion, barley and rice.
Reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 45 to 50 minutes until barley and rice are tender and liquid is absorbed. Add parsley, margarine and lemon peel; toss with fork to blend. Makes 4 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, carrots, bell pepper, onion and egg in a large mixing bowl.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Put ketchup on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a covered baking dish.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in refrigerator to jell.
When serving top with Cool Whip if desired.

title: harvest pumpkin bars
directions: Stir together the dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add pumpkin, oil and eggs.
Mix until smooth. Spread batter evenly in greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Cool and spread with fluffy cream cheese icing.

title: zesty beef stir-fry italiano
directions: In a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat, stir-fry the garlic in oil for 1 minute.
Add the beef; stir-fry for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Season with the pepper.
Remove with a slotted spoon and set aside.
Add zucchini to the same skillet; stir-fry until crisp-tender, 2 to 3 minutes.
Return beef to the skillet; add the tomatoes and dressing and heat through.
Serve over the hot pasta; sprinkle with Parmesan.

title: e z punch
directions: Mix well and add ice.

title: crown jewel dessert
directions: Prepare the three jello's separately, using 1 cup hot water and 1/2 cup cold for each.
Pour into separate 8 x 8-inch pans. Chill until firm and cut into cubes.

title: gorga (danish) pickles
directions: Peel cucumbers and scoop out seeds.
Cut in strips and soak in water with 3 teaspoons salt overnight.
Drain; don't rinse.
Make syrup of 1 1/2 cups vinegar, sugar and water (a little mustard seed and turmeric).
Bring to boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Pack pickles asparagus fashion in sterilized jars.
Pour hot boiling syrup over, full to top and seal.
Before sealing, put sprig of dill in each jar.
Makes about 3 pints.

title: spiced punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot. Bring to a boil. Then reduce to a simmer and serve hot with extra cinnamon sticks for stirring.

title: scotch-a-roos
directions: Mix sugar and white syrup in heavy pan. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat immediately. Add peanut butter, rice krispies. Stir and press in 9X13 pan. Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips in double boiler. Spread over rice krispy mixture.

title: shrimp laced with mild spices(masala jheengari; serves 6)
directions: Bring 1 quart of water to boil.
Add shrimp and turmeric and cook for 4 minutes or just until shrimp turn pink.
Drain shrimp, reserving cooking water.

title: bacon cheddar pinwheels(5 dozen)
directions: Roll bread flat with rolling pin.
In a small bowl, mix milk, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Cut bacon in half.
Lie 3 half-slices of bacon close together on flat surface.
Cover with slice of bread.
Spread 1 to 1 1/2 teaspoons mustard mix over bread.
Sprinkle with cheese, 1 tablespoon.
Roll with bacon on outside; secure each bacon with a toothpick.
Slice in 3 sections. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes on broiler tray.
May serve with mustard/Worcestershire dip.

title: rancho beans
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add to other ingredients (also beans with juices).
Place in baking dish and bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: rice krispie cookies
directions: Cream margarine, oil, brown sugar, white sugar and egg.
Add lemon, vanilla and butter flavoring.
Stir in dry ingredients, adding Rice Krispies last.
Make small balls.
Bake at 350°
for 15 minutes.

title: applesauce raisin cake
directions: Mix the oil, Sweet 'N Low, applesauce, vanilla and water.
In another bowl, sift the flour, cinnamon, cloves, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add 1 cup raisins to dry ingredients and mix well.
Add about half of the dry ingredients to the wet mixture.
Add 1/2 cup sweet milk.
Add remaining dry ingredients. Mix well.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 16-inch Pyrex baking dish for 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: autumn apples
directions: In a medium saucepan, over medium heat, melt butter until foaming.
Add apples, cook 2 minutes, tossing occasionally.
Add honey and sprinkle spices over apples.
Toss gently to combine. Cook until apples are tender, about 3 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar, beat until smooth.
Drop eggs and beat until blended.
Add peanut butter and stir until well blended. Sift flour with soda and salt.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add chocolate chips and make in balls.
Mash with fork.
Bake at 350° about 12 minutes.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add pecans and saut 1 to 2 minutes. In large bowl, combine Eagle Brand, buttered pecans and flavoring; mix well. Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour into ice cream freezer container and freeze according to manufacturer's instructions. Makes 2 quarts. If necessary, add additional milk and 1/2 cup sugar to fill container.

title: easy italian casserole
directions: Cook and stir beef, onion, salt and pepper until brown.
Stir in tomato (spaghetti) sauce.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 4 x 4-inch baking dish. Mix Bisquick per directions on box.
Spread half of Bisquick in pan.
Top with cheese; spoon beef mixture over cheese and top with cheese.
Drop remaining dough by spoonfuls on top.
Bake 20 minutes or until light brown.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well; pat into 2 small loaves onto a large flat pan.
Turn oven to 350°.
Put meat loaf on top rack.
Leave until half-way done, approximately 30 minutes.
Drain grease if any, then add ketchup on top of meat loaf.
Spread across evenly.
Return to oven.
Cook for 20 to 25 minutes longer.
Drain grease if any, then serve.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saut first 4 ingredients with 2 tablespoons margarine 5 minutes. Add both Knorr mixes with specified amount of water from package. Simmer for 10 minutes after bringing to a boil. Add salt and pepper, thyme and Mrs. Dash. Optional: Pure in blender.

title: shenandoah valley broccoli
directions: Cook and drain the broccoli.
Put into 1 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour mixture over the broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: salsa dip
directions: Microwave Velveeta and salsa in 1 1/2-quart microwavable bowl on High 5 minutes or until Velveeta is melted, stirring after 3 minutes. Makes 3 cups.

title: calico beans
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef, bacon, onion and bell pepper; drain.
In large casserole dish, mix with pork and beans, brown sugar and catsup.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: christmas ornaments
directions: Mix ingredients together until they form a ball.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll on a surface sprinkled with allspice and cut with a cookie cutter.
Use straw to make a hole for the hanger.
Let dry 4 to 5 days on a cookie sheet.

title: straight jackets(three variations)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut artichokes in half and cut bacon strips in half to make two shorter pieces.
Wrap bacon around artichokes and secure with a toothpick.
Place on a baking sheet and bake 10-12 minutes or until bacon is crisp.
Drain on a paper towel and serve warm.

title: orange julius
directions: In blender mix ingredients until thick.
Serve the night after blended.

title: steak and onion pie
directions: Roll meat in flour, salt, pepper and all spices.
Brown the meat; add onions and cook until light.
Add the potatoes and brown and stir.
Add hot water and simmer until near tender.
Turn into casserole.
Cover with pie crust.
Brush with beaten egg.
Bake in a 400° to 425° oven for 25 minutes.
Serve with salad and peach cobbler for dessert.

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate and shortening in a small bowl in microwave.
Mix in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Bake until brownies pull away from sides of pan, 30 to 35 minutes. Cool slightly and cut into 2 inch squares.

title: ranchero supper stew
directions: In a large skillet, melt shortening and brown meat.
Add onion soup mix, tomatoes, water and chili powder.
Cook uncovered for 30 minutes.
Add carrots, green pepper, celery and potatoes.
Cook, uncovered, for 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender and gravy is thickened.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix together liquid oil, eggs, vanilla and sugar.
Fold in diced apples and pecans.
Add flour, salt, soda and cinnamon. Stir well.
Pour in Bundt pan (sprayed with Pam).
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° or until done.

title: fried rice
directions: In a skillet, cook meat.
Add green pepper, onion and carrot. Continue cooking until onion cooks, about 1 to 2 minutes.
Add rice in skillet.
Sprinkle soy sauce, stirring constantly.
In skillet, break egg into mixture, stirring until egg cooks. Simmer about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: brown slices
directions: Bake 20
minutes in a moderate oven.
Cool slightly and ice.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Place cutlets between 2 pieces of foil and pound until very thin. Dredge in flour and salt. Shake off excess.
Heat butter and oil. Saute chicken 5 minutes over medium heat, turning meat only once.
If skillet is not large enough, as soon as first slices are done, pile on a plate and keep warm. Return all chicken to skillet, adding the chicken broth. Simmer until the liquid is reduced by half.
Add lemon juice and thin slices of lemon.
Heat only until lemons are hot.
Add parsley at the last minute. Serve with the sauce poured over and garnish with the hot lemon slices.

title: lentil stew
directions: Rinse and drain lentils.
In a large saucepan, combine lentils, chicken broth, undrained tomatoes, potato, carrot, celery, onion, parsley, basil, garlic and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 45 to 50 minutes or until lentils and vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally. Low-fat, no cholesterol.

title: cornsticks for 9 cornstick mold
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Mix the egg and milk and stir into the dry ingredients; add oil.
Drop from teaspoon into greased cornstick mold.
Bake at 425° for 17 minutes.

title: peach cake pie
directions: Place peaches in well-greased 10-inch pie pan or 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice; cover with 2 tablespoons sugar. Cream together butter and remaining 1/2 cup sugar.
Add egg and mix.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; mix with creamed mixture.
Spread over fruit.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 45 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream or ice cream.
Makes 8 to 9 servings.

title: honey beet pickles
directions: Fill jars with beets to within inch of jar rim.
Heat honey, vinegar, cinnamon and cloves to boiling.
Pour over beets to one-half inch of top.
Place lids on; put in water bath.
Process about one hour.
Yields enough juice for 5 pints of packed beets.

title: baked fish fillets
directions: Cut fillets in serving pieces.
Place in greased, shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika, lemon juice, salt and pepper.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Cook spaghetti in
chicken broth. Dice onion, bell pepper and celery.
Saute onion, bell pepper and celery in margarine.
Add Ro-Tel and Velveeta cheese.
Mix with chicken and spaghetti and put in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: summer squash pie
directions: Measure flour and salt into mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening until the size of tiny peas.
Sprinkle gradually with cold water until all particles are moist; roll out and fit into 9-inch pie pan.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt margarine with marshmallows.
Pour mixture over popcorn in a large bowl. Stir in M&M's and peanuts.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch dish with vegetable spray.
Put mixture in dish and spread.
Let it cool and then cut into bars. This can also be made in a Bundt pan.

title: honey mustard chicken tenders
directions: Cut chicken steaks into 3/4-inch strips (easiest to do when partially thawed).
Mix honey and mustard in shallow bowl.
Coat chicken with honey/mustard mix and then roll in bread crumbs.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the first four ingredients.
Then, stir in remaining ingredients.
Divide dough in half, shape each half into roll about 10 inches long by 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill for 4 hours or more.
Slice 1/8-inch thick. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Pour into greased and floured 11 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes (1 hour in tube pan).

title: german potato salad
directions: Combine vinegar, hot water and sugar.
Cook potatoes with skins on until done.
Peel and slice while still warm.
Mix all ingredients together gently, adding olive oil in last.
Crisp cooked bacon may also be added if desired.

title: spicy stir-fry vegetables
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Mix well and set aside. Coat a large skillet or wok with oil. Place over medium-high heat. Stir-fry onions 2 minutes. Add broccoli and carrots; stir-fry 5 minutes. Add mushrooms; stir-fry 2 minutes. Stir in reserved cornstarch mixture. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Makes 8 servings. Each serving contains 77 calories, 1.8 g fat and 4.4 g protein. Exchange is 2 vegetables.

title: watermelon rind pickles
directions: Remove green and pink from watermelon.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
let stand overnight in salt and water.

title: corn on the grill
directions: Pull husk from corn (do not remove).
Remove silks.
Rub corn with butter.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pull husk back over corn and tie top with heavy string.
Cook.
Cover with grill lid over medium hot coals.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes, turning occasionally.
Remove strings and serve immediately.
Yields 12 servings.

title: corn fritters(great for leftover corn.)
directions: Mix corn, onion, egg, parsley and seasonings in a mixing bowl. Add flour to make a thick paste. Add beer, enough to make a thin batter.
Let batter sit for about 15 minutes to thicken slightly. Fry by dropping spoonfuls of batter into hot oil.
(I use a frying pan with about 1-inch of oil.) Turn fritters when golden brown and fry on the other side until done.
Drain on towels. Serve hot, alone or with salsa for dipping.

title: baked chicken italiano
directions: Cut off the wing tips if you are using white meat and remove any fat from the inside of the chicken pieces.
Squeeze the lemon directly onto the chicken and rub the juice in the lemon pieces. Place chicken in a single layer in a shallow baking dish. Sprinkle with the seasoned salt.
Pour the dressing over all chicken.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes, basting frequently.
Raise the heat to 475° and bake for an additional 15 minutes, basting twice.

title: play dough
directions: These ingredients have to be all combined in a large cooking pan under low heat, stirring constantly, as it leaves the side of the pan.
It should be thick enough; pour on wax paper to cool.

title: special k bars
directions: Mix corn syrup and sugar in saucepan; bring to a boil over medium heat.
Stir frequently.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and cereal.
Press mixture into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chips and spread over top.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: summer vegetable medley
directions: In a large bowl, combine butter, parsley, basil, chives, salt and pepper.
Add vegetables, toss to coat.
Place vegetables in disposable foil pan.
Grill covered, over medium-high heat for 5 minutes; stir.
Grill five minutes longer or until vegetables are tender.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in water until tender. Reserve the broth.
When chicken is cool, remove meat from bones and cut into bite size pieces.
Put the chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: pineapple cookies(makes 5 dozen)
directions: Mix thoroughly the first 3 ingredients.
Stir in pineapple. Sift together flour, soda, salt and nutmeg and stir in.
Mix in nuts.
Chill at least one hour.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake until, when touched lightly with finger, no imprint remains at 400° (moderately hot oven) for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: venison casserole
directions: Brown venison and onion.
Drain well.
Add soup, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Heat through.
In 3-quart casserole, layer potatoes, peas and meat, ending with meat.
Pour milk over top. Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are done.

title: shea's holiday dip
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients and blend well. Place in a serving bowl. Cover and allow to chill at least 4 hours to overnight. Serve with flavored crackers. Yields up to 3 cups.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Melt butter in pan.
In a small bowl, mix spices together; then add them to the melted butter.
Mix well; add the ketchup and flour to form a paste.
Add the milk and make sure all spices have dissolved.
Add the cheese in small slices and cook until all cheese is melted, stirring constantly.

title: double peanut clusters
directions: Melt butterscotch pieces and peanut butter in top of double boiler over hot, not boiling, water.
Add nuts; stir until well blended.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper or foil-lined cookie sheet.
Chill until firm.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix altogether.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old fashioned peanut butter sheet cookies
directions: Optional:
You can add M&M's, Reese's pieces or butterscotch chips or all of these.

title: salsa marinara
directions: In a medium-large saucepan over medium heat, cook onion and garlic in the oil, stirring occasionally for 5 minutes. Stir in the tomatoes, sugar and salt and pepper and simmer, covered, stirring occasionally for 25 minutes.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Stir cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Add onions and dried beef.
Good with crackers.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Serve cool or at room temperature.

title: e.z. oat crust
directions: Lightly spray 9-inch pie plate with nonstick cooking spray or grease lightly.
Combine oats, flour, melted margarine and brown sugar, mixing well.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Do not peel zucchini, wash and cut and remove seeds.
Add onion, pepper, garlic and salt.
Cover with cracked ice.
Mix and stand 3 hours.
Drain.
Combine vinegar, spices, sugar, chilies and liquid.
Heat to boil.
Add zucchini and reheat to boil.
Lower heat and simmer briefly.
Process.
Makes 10 pints plus.

title: pasta with spinach and shrimp(serves 2)
directions: Wash, drain and chop spinach.

title: jalapeno cheese squares
directions: Spray bottom of 9 1/2 x 13-inch baking pan with Pam cooking spray. Line bottom of pan with jalapeno slices to taste. (May use slices of black or green olives or crumbled bacon instead.) Layer grated Cheddar cheese and Monterey Jack cheese over jalapeno peppers. Beat eggs and pour over. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean. Cut into small squares and serve as an appetizer. Serve warm.

title: pineapple dressing
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg and then pineapple.
Mix well. Fold in bread.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crab stuffed avocado
directions: Mix the crab meat, celery, mayonnaise, chili sauce and lemon juice.
Split the avocados; remove the pits and sprinkle avocado halves with lemon juice and stuff with the crab meat mixture. Serve on lettuce-lined plates with crackers and fresh fruit. Serves 8.

title: green rice
directions: Mix together rice, onions, peppers, parsley, salad oil, cheese and garlic.
Put into casserole dish and pour the milk over mixture.
Sprinkle seasoned salt on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until top starts to brown.

title: easy corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Mix other ingredients and add to buttered dish.
Bake at 350° until knife comes out clean.
For large gatherings, recipe may be doubled.
Serves 6.

title: chicken scampi
directions: Cut chicken breast into small strips (1/2 to 1-inch wide). Dredge in flour.
Melt four tablespoons of margarine and oil in a large skillet.
Saute chicken until lightly browned.
Remove chicken from pan.

title: hot fruit salad
directions: Arrange pineapple chunks, pears, peaches, apricots, halves and cherries in a large baking dish or 11 x 14-inch or 3-quart flat. Mix cornstarch, brown sugar, curry powder and melted butter with fruit juices. Stir over low heat until consistency of a light cream sauce; pour over fruit and add pecans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Serve hot.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs; beat well.
Add the next 5 ingredients; beat well.
Fold in carrots and nuts.
Pour into a greased angel food cake pan.
Bake at 300° for 60 minutes.
Beat the cream cheese, butter, icing sugar and vanilla until creamy; ice the Carrot Cake when cool.

title: basic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut shortening into flour until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add enough milk to make a soft dough. Stir with a fork only until dough leaves side of bowl.
Turn dough out onto lightly floured board and knead just until smooth.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness and cut with cutter.
Place biscuits on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: 5 flavor pound cake
directions: Blend all ingredients in large mixing bowl; mix well.
Place in cold oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes (until toothpick comes out clean).
Cool on wire rack.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Whip all until creamy.

title: play dough for christmas decorations
directions: Knead all ingredients for 5 minutes.
Roll out dough.
Cut into desired shapes with cookie cutters.
Poke a hole into top of ornaments with a straw.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for about 2 hours.
Paint ornaments with tempra paint.
Varnish each ornament to seal out moisture.

title: robert redford desserts
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: latkes
directions: Coarsely grate potatoes and onion; drain any liquid. Place in a bowl; add green onions, egg, salt and pepper. In an electric skillet, heat 1/8-inch of oil to 375°. Drop batter by heaping tablespoonfuls into hot oil. Flatten to form patties. Fry until golden brown; turn and cook the other side. Drain on paper towels. Serve with applesauce. Yield: 2 dozen.

title: jam heart scones
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Beat egg slightly in medium bowl.
Stir in milk, applesauce, butter and almond extract. Stir in remaining ingredients, except preserves and powdered sugar, just until moistened.

title: rainbow divinity
directions: Mix sugar, water and corn syrup.
Cook to 265° on candy thermometer.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Gradually add dry Jell-O.
Beat until mixture holds peak.
Slowly add hot syrup while continuing to beat.
Beat until candy loses its gloss.
Stir in nuts and coconut.
Drop into small mounds on foil.

title: cookie on a stick
directions: You will need popsicle sticks.

title: aunt cleo's chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken breasts and roll in flour. Brown on top of stove in small amount of Crisco. Add a little butter when browning. Dilute can of cream of chicken soup with 1/2 cup milk. Put in heavy skillet with tight lid.
Heat to a boil, then reduce heat to low and cook approximately 1 hour. Test with fork after 45 minutes.

title: dressing for slaw
directions: Place sugar, flour, mustard and cider vinegar in saucepan; mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes (after it starts to boil).
Remove from heat and add onion.
Add slowly and beat briskly as you add salad oil and celery seed.
Keeps in refrigerator a long time.
Shake before using.

title: creamy horseradish dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender until well blended.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: paris hilton's lasagne recipe
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain. Start with a layer of noodles and continue with other ingredients. Layer in this order until all is used up. Bake until all is done. Noodles will bake done.

title: veggie casserole
directions: In large pot, boil broccoli until soft.
Cut potatoes into cubes.
Pour broccoli and potatoes into baking dish.
Pour in remaining ingredients.
Crush crackers and spread over mixture. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: blueberry and lemon bread
directions: Cream butter, gradually add sugar; add eggs.
Combine dry ingredients; add to cream mixture, alternating with milk.
Stir in lemon rind, fold in berries and pour in loaf pan.
Bake for 55 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well and place in casserole dish.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Whip all ingredients together.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until a knife inserted in the middle comes out clean.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, margarine and pecans and press in baking dish.
Bake at 350° until light brown (about 15 minutes).
Cool completely.

title: chicken chalupas
directions: In a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole, place 1/2 crushed tortilla chips.
Saute onion until tender and add both soups, milk and picante sauce.
Cook over low heat until well blended.
Spoon half of soup mixture over Tostitos chips, then sprinkle with 1 cup chicken and half cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cola punch
directions: The day before serving, combine lemon juice, lemon rind and sugar.
Mix well. Refrigerate, covered.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Place onion in shallow pan.
Put chicken on top,
single layer with skin side up.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350°
for about 1 hour.

title: five flavor cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, which have been beaten until thick and lemon-colored (about 5 minutes).
Combine flour and baking powder and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in flavorings.
Spoon mixture into greased 10-inch tube pan and bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Work together with fingers.
Pat dough into small cakes, 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick.
Bake on ungreased sheets at 325° for 25 minutes. Turn oven up to 350° and brown for 5 minutes.
Watch closely, so they don't get too brown.
Cut immediately on cookie sheet and cool.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 4 to 5 cakes.
Doubles easily.

title: lemon chiffon
directions: Stir hot water into Jell-O; add lemon extract.
Let cool and set until slightly thick.
Whip milk until thick.
Add sugar gradually.
Fold into Jell-O.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Use 10 x 13-inch pan.
Serves 24.

title: cheese ball
directions: Work all together in bowl with your hands.
Roll in a ball in crushed nuts.
Refrigerate or freeze.
Good at holiday time!

title: poor man's cake
directions: Simmer for 15 minutes and let cool the raisins and water. Cream the sugar, shortening and cold water.
Add flour, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and baking soda.
Add raisins and juice (if needed).
Mix up real good.
Pour in 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: caramels
directions: Generously butter a 9 x 9 x 2 inch pan; set aside.
In a heavy 3 quart saucepan melt the butter.
Add sugar and dash salt; stir thoroughly.
Stir in corn syrup.
Gradually add condensed milk; stir constantly.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, to 245° (firm-ball stage), for 15 to 20 minutes (mixture should boil gently over entire surface).
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla. Pour into buttered pan.
When cool, cut into squares with a wet, sharp knife.
Wrap each piece in clear plastic wrap.
Makes about 2 1/2 pounds.

title: blackberry or raspberry jam
directions: Crush berries one layer at a time.
Measure fruit packed solidly in cup; if slightly short add water.
Put into 6 to 8-quart pan.
Measure sugar and set aside.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Stir above together and chill for several hours.

title: apple cider punch
directions: Combine the orange and lemon juices with the cider and dissolve the powdered sugar in the mixture thoroughly.
Just before serving, add the carbonated grape juice and serve in iced glasses.
Serves 5.

title: peanut butter marshmallow fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in a large, heavy saucepan. Bring to a boil and allow to boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and peanut butter; stir until melted.
Spread in a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Allow to cool.
Cut into squares when firm.
Yields 3 pounds.

title: crawfish fettucine
directions: In medium size bowl, place margarine and onion.
Cook 3 minutes on High.
Add whipping cream, flour and seasoning.
Cover with Saran Wrap and cook 2 minutes.
Stir and cook 3 minutes. Serve on cooked noodles.

title: baked winter squash
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Cut the squash in half and remove seeds.
Sprinkle the cut sides with salt.
