Place cut side down on a baking dish and bake for about 40 to 50 minutes, until easily pierced with a fork.

title: corn and rice casserole
directions: In large Dutch oven, cook onions in butter until tender.
Add corn and jalapenos.
Mix well and heat for 7 minutes.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Add cooked rice.
Spoon into 9 x 13 casserole dish and bake in 350° oven for about 25 minutes.

title: clam chowder
directions: In large pan, melt butter.
Add onion and celery.
Cook until tender.
Add flour and make a roux.
In separate pan heat clam broth.
Add roux to broth.
Whisk until thickened.
Whisk into pan the clams, bouillon cubes and bacon.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Add potatoes.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Heat half and half in separate pan.
Add to chowder.
Stir and serve immediately.

title: batter-fried vegetables
directions: In bowl, stir together first five ingredients.
Stir in water and egg until smooth.
Pour corn oil into large skillet to depth of 1/2-inch, filling no more than 1/3 full.
Heat over medium heat to 375°.
Dip vegetables a few at a time, into batter.
(Stir batter occasionally.) Carefully add vegetables to hot oil, a few pieces at a time.
Fry, turning once, 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown and crisp.
Drain on paper towels.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees. Grease sheet cake or casserole pan. In a large bowl, sift together flour sugar, baking powder and salt. Stir in caraway seeds. Cut in butter until coarse cornmeal stage. Stir in raisins. Place milk, egg and baking soda in small bowl; beat together until well blended. Turn onto floured board; knead 3 minutes until smooth. Shape into ball. Place on baking sheet or casserole. cut an X 1/2 inch deep into the top. Beat egg white and water together; brush on top of dough (optional). Bake 60-65 minutes. Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan and cool on rack completely. Enjoy with your favorite soup, stew or chowder.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine milk, pudding mix, sour cream and half of the Cool Whip. Beat until thick. Layer bottom of large baking dish with vanilla wafers. Pour half of the pudding mixture over wafers. Slice bananas on top. Add remaining pudding. Place wafers around edges and crumble some on top. Finally, top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Mix Crisco and margarine.
Add sugar.
Cream until smooth. Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add flavoring.
Mix cocoa with flour. Add flour and milk.
Mix well.
Pour into large tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Start with cold oven.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook onion in a little hot fat until golden.
Add meat and seasoning.
Brown.
Add drained beans and soup.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mash potatoes.
Add milk, eggs and seasonings.
Spoon in mounds over meat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: brunch bake(strata - breakfast)
directions: Place 6 slices of bread (trimmed)
in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch
baking dish.
Cover with
slices
of
cheese.
Add layer of chipped ham, cooked and	crumbled
bacon
or
browned sausage meat.
Add another layer of cheese.
Beat
6 eggs; add 3 cups of milk, salt and pepper.
Pour
over	layered mixture. Refrigerate overnight.	Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: surprise pie
directions: Add sugar gradually to margarine; cream until fluffy.
Add syrup and salt; beat well.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in coconut and oats.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 50 minutes.
Cool.

title: dilly bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Heat to lukewarm the cottage cheese and butter.
Add yeast to lukewarm cottage cheese mixture. Mix all dry ingredients together.
Stir dry ingredients into wet mixture to form a soft dough.
Place in bowl in warm place; let rise to double in bulk (about an hour).
Punch down and place in greased loaf pan.
Let rise a second time for about 30 minutes. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix broccoli, corn and onion with egg, salt and pepper.
Put in casserole.
Toss bread crumbs with melted butter and put on top.
Top with raw bacon cut in 1-inch squares.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: carlo peraldo's recipe for lumpy tomato sauce
directions: Chop onion, pepper and celery very coarsely; saute in heavy saucepan with olive oil until tender.
Cut stewed tomatoes into quarters and add to the vegetables along with the tomato sauce and Italian seasoning.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, about 1 hour or until sauce thickens.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: 5 hour stew
directions: Mix.
Bake covered at 250° for 5 hours.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Melt oleo and add broccoli and onion.
Saute and cover until onion is transparent and broccoli cooked.
Add soup, cheese, milk and cooked rice.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: boiled raisin cake
directions: Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together. Chill 2 hours. Serve in Hawaiian bread.

title: native american cornbread
directions: In 9-inch iron skillet, fry bacon crisp.
Reserve 2 tablespoons fat and throw rest away.
Heat oven to 350°.

title: frosty pumpkin pie
directions: Spread soft ice cream in baked pie crust.
Put in freezer. Mix pumpkin, sugar, spices, salt and nuts.
Beat whipping cream until stiff.
Fold into pie mixture.
Pour over ice cream in pie shell.
Freeze several hours.
Remove 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine eggs, milk and then add cracker crumbs.
Set aside until absorbed.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese, to mixture.
Stir well and place in a quart casserole (round or square).
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 4 or 5.

title: margarete edgerton norris' yeast breaddallas, texas
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 pt. luke warm water, add sugar and mix up sponge using flour, enough to be not runny, not thick.
When it rises, put in salt and lard and mix up stiff and knead until dough is smooth and easy to handle.
Let rise, punch down, rise again and make out loaves.
Let rise and bake about an hour at 325°. Loaves will come loose from pan when done.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion and green pepper.
Saute.
Pour off extra grease.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together in bean pot or big Pyrex dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: one dish meal
directions: Put into 9 inch square casserole dish and cover with 1 can of mushroom soup.
Bake covered for 1 1/2 hours at 350 degrees.

title: chicken-cornbread casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5 people.

title: seafood okra gumbo
directions: Cook shrimp in 2 quarts of water for about 30 minutes.
Shell shrimp and save the broth.
Cover bottom of a large pot with oil and add okra, onions, green pepper and garlic.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently until vegetables are done.
(Vegetables are done when okra stops roping.)
Add tomatoes and stir to blend. Add shrimp broth, oyster liquid, bay leaf and seasonings.
Add shrimp and crab meat and simmer 45 minutes.
Add oysters and cook until done, approximately 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve in gumbo or soup bowls over rice.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine all ingredients and put topping on.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in pineapple, break up bread and fold in.
Bake in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish for 1 hour at 350°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil together.
Add vanilla, flour, nuts and apples.
This will be thick.
Bake at 325° in tube pan or loaf pan for 1 1/2 hours in tube pan or 35 to 40 minutes in loaf pan.

title: high-fiber chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar;
add the vanilla and eggs and beat well.
Mix
the flour, Bran and baking soda together, then add
this dry mixture alternately with water;
beat well. Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonfuls onto baking sheet. Bake at 375° for about 8 minutes.

title: pineapple pork sweet and sour
directions: Dip pork in beaten egg.
Combine flour, Accent and salt in bag.
Add pork and shake.
In large skillet, heat enough oil to fry the pork.
Fry pork for 6 to 8 minutes or until well browned. Remove and drain.
In skillet, combine chicken broth, soy sauce, sugar, pineapple syrup, catsup and vinegar and bring to boil.
Mix cornstarch (4 teaspoons) with 4 teaspoons cold water.
Stir into sauce, cooking until it thickens.
Add pork, pineapple, onions and bell pepper.
Cook, stirring rapidly, for about 4 minutes.
Serve with hot rice.

title: butter pecan cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together (do not use electric mixer) and pour into well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Cool at least 30 minutes before turning out of pan.

title: dill pickles
directions: Scrub cucumbers.
Place a layer of dill on bottom of large ceramic bowl or crock.
Cover with half the cucumbers.
Add another layer of dill, then the remaining cucumbers.
Add garlic. Top with final layer of dill.

title: pink fling
directions: Boil pineapple and sugar for 5 minutes.
Add jello.
Let cool. Mix whipped topping and cream cheese together until well blended. Add jello mixture.
Put in glass dish and refrigerate until firm.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Put in a large pan.
Cover with 3 tablespoons salt.
Let stand one hour.
Drain.
Mix 2 cups sugar, 1 cup vinegar and 1 teaspoon celery seed.
Pour over pickles.
Let stand 3 days before eating.

title: double chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine pie filling mix, milk, butter and chips in saucepan. Cook and stir the mixture over medium heat until mixture comes to a full bubbling boil.
Remove from heat.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into pie shell.
Place plastic wrap lightly over pie to avoid skin from forming.
Refrigerate 3 hours.
Garnish with whipped topping and grated chocolate.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Warm the jar of marshmallow cream in hot water.
Bake a yellow cake.
Spread marshmallow cream on top of cake as soon as you take it out of oven (carefully).
Let set.
Melt the margarine, cocoa, milk and vanilla over low heat; stir well.
Mix in the powdered sugar; pour over cake.

title: delta cheesecake
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Blend cream cheese, eggs, 1/2 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons vanilla together. Spoon into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix sour cream, 2 teaspoons vanilla and 1/2 cup sugar together.
Spoon over cream cheese mixture.
Return to oven; bake at 400° for 5 minutes. Remove and chill thoroughly. Can top with your favorite fresh or canned fruit.
Serves 6.

title: scampi-style shrimp
directions: In a large skillet over medium-high heat, cook and stir green onion and garlic in margarine and oil 1 minute.
Add shrimp; cook and stir until shrimp are pink.
Add ReaLemon and salt; heat through.
Garnish with parsley.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Line bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish with croutons. Cover with sausage.
Beat eggs.
Combine remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Pour over croutons and meat.
Top with cheese. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: oats and pumpkin pinwheels
directions: Beat 1 cup of sugar and margarine until fluffy.
Mix in egg whites.
Stir in flour, oats and baking soda.
On wax paper, press into a 16 x 12-inch rectangle.
Spread combined pumpkin, 1/4 cup of sugar and spice over dough to 1/2 inch from edge.
From narrow end, roll up dough.
Sprinkle sesame seed around roll, pressing gently.
Wrap in wax paper; freeze overnight or until firm.

title: milky way homemade ice cream
directions: Melt Milky Way bars in top of double boiler.
Add syrup and Eagle Brand milk.
Stir well.
Cool.
Add milk and pour into freezer compartment of 4-quart freezer.
Add milk to fill line. Freeze as for regular ice cream.

title: tasty salmon
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form into small patties.
Place in skillet of hot oil and fry until golden brown.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together cheese and marshmallows at medium speed until fluffy. Add a splash of orange juice or lemon (optional). Serve with fruit.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and cocoa in a pan.
Stir in sugar.
Add one egg at a time.
Stir in flour and vanilla.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken in casserole dish.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes uncovered.

title: dump salad
directions: Do not dissolve gelatin.
Add dry gelatin to the pineapple and cottage cheese.
Stir to blend well.
Fold in prepared Cool Whip. Chill mixture for 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: brie appetizer spreads
directions: Very lightly skim off the top of the brie cheese.

title: strawberry truffles
directions: Set out frozen strawberries to thaw.
Cook the white cake mix, then set to cool.
Pour the strawberry jello into a big glass bowl; set in refrigerator for 1 1/2 hours.
Then cook the vanilla pudding.
When that's all done, set white cake on top of jello. Spread pudding on top of cake.
Then add strawberries and Cool Whip.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Add all ingredients together, except cheese; mix well.
Grease an 8 x 4-inch pan.
Add 1/2 cup cheese into bread mixture.
Pour into pan.
Spread other 1/2 cup cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sandy's strawberry jello
directions: Mix jello with boiling water.
Add strawberries, pineapple and bananas.
Pour half mixture in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Add sour cream.
Pour rest of jello on top.
Chill.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Mix both kinds of cheese and set aside. Break spaghetti into 3-inch lengths. Cook and drain. Cook meat and drain off fat. Add onions and peppers. Put meat mixture into a large bowl. Sprinkle with salt. Gradually stir in soup, milk and 1 cup shredded cheese. Add cooked spaghetti. Pour into 9 x 13 casserole dish. Sprinkle remaining cheese over top. Bake, uncovered, approximately 1 hour at 350° until heated through. May be refrigerated overnight before baking. Serves 12 to 15.

title: onion soup
directions: In a large saucepan over low heat, melt margarine.
Add onion and cook, stirring frequently, 15 minutes.
Add flour and cook, stirring constantly, 1 minute.
Add broth and pepper; bring to a boil.

title: meatless vegetable all italian soup
directions: Melt butter in 4-quart pot.
Stir in onions and cabbage.
Heat 2 minutes.
Add water, cover and simmer another 10 minutes.
Stir in veggies, tomatoes and seasonings. Simmer 10 minutes.
If using frozen or fresh veggies, simmer until tender.

title: cinnamon bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk.
Sift flour and cinnamon together.
Add flour to creamed mixture.
Pat into an ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Pour unbeaten egg white over entire surface; drain off any excess.
Sprinkle nuts on tops, pressing in slightly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut into bars while still moderately warm.

title: lemon ice cream pie
directions: Combine margarine, lemon rind, lemon juice, salt, 1 cup sugar and eggs in double boiler until thick.
Cool.
Place half of custard in baked pie shell.
Top with half of the ice cream. Freeze, then add rest of custard and ice cream.
Refreeze.

title: tuna or salmon salad sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients, refrigerate long enough to cool.
Serve on lightly toasted slices of sourdough bread.
(Use tuna packed in water.)

title: cinnamon popcorn
directions: Put popped popcorn in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt butter, cinnamon, salt and sugar in a pan.
Cook slowly just until the sugar dissolves (don't boil).
Pour over popcorn; stir thoroughly. Put in a 300° oven for 15 minutes.

title: carrot cake ring
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch Bundt pan. Into a large bowl, measure first 11 ingredients.
With mixer at low speed, beat ingredients just until mixed, constantly scraping bowl with rubber spatula.
Increase speed to high.
Beat 4 minutes, occasionally scraping bowl.

title: fluffy fruit salad
directions: Dissolve pudding in crushed pineapple.
Add fruit cocktail and mandarin oranges.
Fold in whipped topping.
Add marshmallows. Let sit several hours or overnight in refrigerator before serving.

title: dixieland delight
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown sausage, onion and bell pepper; drain well.
Cut biscuits into 1/4 pieces.
Place pieces of biscuits from one can on bottom of Bundt pan.
Spoon less than 1/2 of sausage mixture over biscuits, then add less than 1/2 of cheese.
Repeat layers and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks.
Beat well.
Add sour cream and baking soda.
Mix well.
Add flour gradually, then the beaten egg whites.
Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes at 300°.

title: sour cream crisps
directions: Blend butter, sugar, eggs and flavoring until light and fluffy.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add alternately with sour cream to first mixture.
Blend well.
Drop from a teaspoon into greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until evenly brown.
Remove cookies to rack for cooling.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add egg yolks and vanilla.
Beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with graham cracker crumbs and milk.
Add nut meats. Fold in egg whites. Bake in two waxed paper lined 8-inch layer cake pans in moderate oven at 350° for 25 minutes.
Put together with Cream Filling and frost with Brown Sugar Frosting.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: german slaw
directions: Chop
cabbage (not too fine).
Mix cabbage, bell pepper and onions.
Heat
oil, sugar, vinegar, salt, celery salt and black pepper until sugar is dissolved.
Pour hot mixture over cabbage mixture.
Refrigerate
for 24 hours.
Makes 2 quarts. Will keep in refrigerator for several weeks.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Melt sugar and butter in skillet until golden brown.
Add cream slowly and cook about 2 minutes. Add vanilla.

title: zucchini bread(this recipe is low-fat and low sugar.)
directions: In a large bowl, combine whole wheat flour, white flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
In a medium bowl, mix together the egg white, whole egg, oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Add this mixture to flour mixture, stirring the ingredients to combine them well.
Stir in nuts and/or raisins and/or sunflower seeds, if desired.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake bread in a preheated 350° oven for 50 or 60 minutes, or until a pick inserted in the center of bread comes out clean.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Tear tortillas into halves.
Set half of them aside.
Cover bottom of casserole dish with the other half.
Brown meat and onion together and season to taste.
Add tomatoes to meat mixture.
Mix well.
Spread this mixture over tortillas in casserole dish. Spread beans over the meat.
Slice cheese and cover entire casserole.
Put second half of tortillas over cheese; spread mushroom soup over all (undiluted).
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Uncover for 10 minutes to brown.

title: zesty cocktail wieners
directions: Cut wieners into 1-inch pieces. Combine rest of the ingredients into saucepan. Bring to simmering boil and add wieners.
Simmer until wieners are tender.
Refrigerate overnight in sauce. Serve in chafing dish and use toothpicks to serve.

title: manhattan clam dip(makes about 2 cups)
directions: In small mixer bowl, beat cheese and mayonnaise until smooth. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with assorted fresh vegetables or potato chips.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Place clams and 1/4 cup clam liquid in a 1-quart covered glass dish.
Microwave on High 5 minutes.
Stir cream cheese and butter into clams.
Cook on High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Stir until smooth. Serve hot with crackers or chips.
Makes 3 cups.

title: date-nut roll
directions: Cook the sugar and cream to soft ball stage.
Add the dates; cook to firm ball stage.
Add the nuts and salt.
Cool.
Beat until mixture can be formed into a roll.
Wrap in wax paper. Chill; slice.

title: fried cauliflower
directions: Break cauliflower into flowerets and cook in salted water until tender.
Drain.
While this is cooking, mix flour, salt, baking powder and eggs.
Add enough water to make a real thin batter.
Coat cauliflower in batter and fry real quick in hot salad oil on both sides.
If any batter is left over, drop by heaping spoonfuls into hot oil
and fry on both sides. Delicious!!!
Drain on absorbent paper.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 the pecans.
Form into a ball or log.
Roll in remaining pecans to coat the outside.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: beef 'n' wine
directions: Put meat in 3-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with garlic powder (you determine amount).
In separate bowl mix together soup, dry soup mix and sherry.
Pour over meat and mix.
Cover casserole and bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Serve over noodles.

title: cowgirl casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Cook macaroni and cheese.
Add tomato sauce, corn, macaroni and garlic salt to the beef.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and butter together. Press into 9 x 13 (greased) pan, bring up on
sides. Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs, powdered sugar, vanilla (can use lemon), pour in crust. Bake at 350° 35 - 40 minutes.

title: deluxe german potato salad
directions: In skillet, cook bacon until crisp. Drain, reserving 1/4 cup drippings. Crumble bacon and set aside. Saute the celery and onion in drippings until tender. Combine sugar and flour; add to skillet with vinegar, water, salt and mustard. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles. In a large bowl, combine potatoes, carrots and parsley; pour the sauce over and stir gently to coat. Season to taste with additional salt, if needed. Spoon into serving dish; garnish with crumbled bacon. Serve warm. Serves 10 to 12.

title: cherry delite
directions: Make a graham cracker crust and put in 8-inch square pan.
Let cheese soften; beat with mixer until fluffy and gradually add Eagle Brand, vanilla and lemon juice.
Put in chilled crust and top with cherry pie filling and chill.

title: chocolate swirl cheesecake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, cinnamon and butter, mixing well.
Firmly press into bottom and up sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan, then refrigerate.
Place chocolate in top of a double boiler; bring water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cook until chocolate melts.
Set aside to cool slightly.
Beat cream cheese with electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Gradually add sugar, mixing well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in flour, lemon rind, lemon juice and vanilla. Fold in whipped cream.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Beat first 2 ingredients until blended.
Gradually add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and vanilla.
Spread in buttered 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: country chicken soup
directions: Cook chicken breast; remove skin and bones.
Shred, then put chicken back in broth.
Get veggies ready while chicken is cooking.
Get potatoes, celery, carrots and onions.
Dice up and cook together.
When done, pour in chicken and broth; throw a handful of egg noodles in soup.
When noodles get tender, dump in small can of peas.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with cornbread.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Look cranberries to pick out bad ones. Put cranberries, apples and oranges in the food processor. Be careful to not make mush. Should be crunchy. Add jello to 2 cups boiling water and then add the sugar. Stir until dissolved. Add the processed fruit and pecans. Mix well. Chill until set.

title: hot mustard cheese bread
directions: Cut bread into 20 slices, cutting to, but not through, bottom crust.
Combine butter, onion, mustard, bacon and poppy seed. Spread on both sides of bread slices.
Cut cheese slices in half diagonally.
Place cheese triangles between bread slices.
Wrap bread in foil.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot. Makes 18 to 20 servings.

title: fondant mints
directions: Add all together except sugar.
Mix with beater until well blended.
Add sugar slowly.
Beat and knead until well mixed. Press into molds.

title: hot cocoa
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and salt in 2-quart saucepan.
Add water; heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 2 minutes. Stir in milk; heat just until hot (do not boil).
Beat with hand beater until foamy or stir until smooth.
Serve immediately. Makes 9 servings.

title: cherry delight dessert
directions: Use large rectangular (approximately 9 x 13-inch) glass pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Mix cherry pie filling and crushed pineapple together.
Pour into pan.
Pour dry cake mix evenly over fruit.
Pat down lightly.
Pour pecans over top.
Pour melted butter evenly over cake and fruit mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Watch and don't let nuts get too brown.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Put cranberries and chili sauce in pot.
Make small meatballs. Drop in sauce.
Cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: cinnamon apple rings
directions: *I recommend Delicious apples, they stay firmer in the syrup.

title: broccoli cheese biscuits
directions: Flatten biscuits and put in muffin pan. Mix all the ingredients except cheese and spoon a big Tbsp. of mixture in each muffin cup. Sprinkle grated cheese on top and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: polish style city chicken or pork chops
directions: You will need aluminum foil.

title: luscious rice pudding
directions: Cook rice in water 10 minutes; do not drain.
Add milk, cream and margarine.
Cook until tender, 30 minutes or more.
Turn off heat.
Add beaten eggs, vanilla and sugar.
Stir.
Return to heat for 2 or 3 minutes, stirring.
Add raisins.
Pour into casserole and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Heat margarine in 2-quart saucepan until melted.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in broth and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole. Cook uncovered in 350° oven until bubbly, 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sunshine salad
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine sugar and gelatin; add hot water and stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Chill until slightly thickened. Add pineapple, mandarin oranges and sour cream.

title: piccalilli
directions: Mix all together in large pan.
Cook over medium temperature to a good boil.
Continue cooking for 5 minutes.
Seal in pint jars for future use.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in food processor.
Chop until fine. Add sugar to taste.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Use a large stew or soup pan. Cook the frozen potatoes in about 2 quarts of water.
Bring to a boil and cook until tender. Drain off some of the water, then add soup and cubed Velveeta cheese.
You can add more water or milk to make desired thickness of soup.
Season with salt or pepper.
Serve with cornbread or crackers.

title: chicken salad
directions: Bake or boil chicken until it is easy to pull apart.
Take the meat off the bones. Take your hands and crumble meat together. Add mayonnaise and pickles.

title: 11 minute peanut brittle
directions: Pour 2 cups apple butter or pureed fruit (any kind) onto a lightly greased jelly roll pan; spread 1/4-inch thick.
Pop in a 175° oven.
Keep the door open slightly so steam escapes.
Check the leather every hour or until it is dry enough to peel.
Cut leather crosswise into 6 pieces.
Lay pieces on plastic wrap and roll jellyroll style.
Store in closed jar.

title: triple good bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In medium saucepan, combine the first 4 ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until mixture begins to bubble.
Remove from heat; cool slightly and set aside.

title: easy bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs well.
Add oil and buttermilk.
Add all to dry ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Can be kept in fridge and baked as needed for a couple of weeks.

title: rotel chicken
directions: In large skillet, melt oleo.
Add onion, bell pepper, tomatoes and chicken; stir.
Add egg noodles; stir.
Pour into large casserole.
Bake for approximately 15 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: homemade eagle brand milk
directions: Select good, ripe peaches.
Scald and peel peaches.
Slice them.
Pour pineapple juice (unsweetened) over peaches and let set a few minutes.
Put in boxes and freeze.

title: lemon-sesame turkey cutlets
directions: In small bowl, stir lemon juice, honey and soy sauce.
Set aside.
Sprinkle each cutlet with pepper.
Place turkey in skillet over medium heat.
Turn after 2 to 3 minutes.
Cook for 2 to 3 more minutes.
Pour lemon juice mixture over turkey; bring to a boil.
Before serving, sprinkle with sesame seed.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Cook broccoli and rice following directions on the boxes. Melt butter and cook onion in butter for 5 minutes.
Mix together in a casserole dish rice, broccoli, butter, onion, cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup and cheese, cut in chunks. Place in oven at 400° and cook until bubbly.

title: german cabbage rolls
directions: Core and boil cabbage and as leaves wilt, peel off and drain. Then place mixture in cabbage leaves and stuff good; roll.
Bake with strips of bacon on top.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Add soda and salt to flour.
Cream shortening; add sugar and eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add milk and flour.
Stir in nuts, cherries and dates.
Chill several hours.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add flour and eggs one at a time. Add coconut (optional).
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cheesy chicken enchiladas
directions: Divide chicken evenly between tortillas.
Combine sour cream, soup, and cheese.
Place rounded tablespoon over chicken in center of tortilla.
Roll tortilla and place seam side down in 9
X 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with remaining sauce.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: pepper hash
directions: Grind peppers and onions fine and place in colander.
Pour boiling water over and drain.
Add salt, sugar and vinegar; boil for 15 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: fruit cheesecake
directions: Place milk in freezer.
Mix lemon juice and water, Equal and gelatin.
Cook and stir until gelatin dissolves.
Cool.
Blend cottage cheese until smooth.
Stir in gelatin mix and vanilla. Chill until partially set.
Whip frozen milk until it peaks.
Fold fruit into partially set cheese.
Fold into whipped milk.
Spoon into square cake pan.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix in saucepan the sugar and cornstarch.
Stir water in gradually.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil 1 minute, then slowly stir at least half of the hot mixture into the 3 beaten egg yolks.
Blend back into hot mixture in saucepan.
Boil 1 minute longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Continue stirring until smooth and blend in the butter, lemon juice and lemon rind.

title: best chocolate syrup brownies(makes 16-18)
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and eggs until very creamy. Add salt, stir in flour, mixing well. Add chocolate syrup, vanilla and chopped nuts. Put in well greased and lightly floured 9 inch square pan. Smooth top. Bake 350° for 35 minutes. Cool in pan or wire rack, but loosen brownies on edge. Cut in squares. Garnish with walnuts or dust with powdered sugar.

title: scripture cake
directions: Follow Solomon's advice for making good boys and you will have a good cake.
Bake at 370° until done.

title: danish puff
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients.
Mix to soft dough.
Pat into pan to make 2 long strips.

title: saturday night chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken pieces with salt, pepper and garlic salt on both sides.
Lay in baking pan.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Mix mushroom soup with whipping cream, parsley flakes and 1 soup can of water.
Pour over chicken.	Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour and 15 to 30 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients for 8 minutes, stirring constantly. Cool a little; add butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Store in covered jar in refrigerator.
This sauce can be heated by placing jar in a pan of boiling water for a few minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat; put in bottom of casserole dish.
Slice potatoes (like a potato chip) on top of meat.
Add a layer of peas and carrots, canned or frozen.
Top with cream of mushroom soup. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix in a bowl the apples, oil, eggs and sugar.
Add the flour, cinnamon, baking soda, vanilla, salt, raisins and walnut meats. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan at 325° for at least one hour.

title: grama underhill's molasses cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg and molasses while shortening is warm.
Add dry ingredients.
Roll into balls, then roll in sugar. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: the bridle path breakfast casserole
directions: Layer potatoes in buttered baking dish.
Top with sausage, 1 cup cheese, and ham.
Beat eggs with mustard, salt, pepper, and milk in bowl.
Pour over top layer.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup of cheese.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.
Serve with toast or banana bread.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Add ingredients as listed.
Cover with ketchup before baking. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry pepper roast
directions: Score meat in a crisscross pattern.
Rub sides only with pepper.
Place in Dutch oven or roasting pan and brown over medium heat on all sides about 15 minutes.
Pour cranberry juice over meat; add cranberries.
Cover and cook in 325° oven for 2 hours until tender.
Place meat on warm platter; add a small amount of cornstarch to juice and cook until thickened.
Makes 8 servings.

title: gramma's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add well-beaten eggs; add baking soda to sour milk.
Add milk and flour alternating.
Add the cinnamon, oatmeal and chopped raisins.
Drop by spoonfuls on a buttered pan and bake in a hot oven.

title: homemade bath salts
directions: Mix well.
Use more or less perfume, as desired.

title: cream sauce for shrimp, lobster or chicken
directions: Using a double boiler, make a thick white sauce of the milk, flour and butter.
Add green pepper, pimento, onion, Worcestershire sauce, red pepper and salt.
Mix egg yolks and cream, then add to sauce just before stirring in mushrooms and shrimp, lobster or chicken.
Make just before serving.

title: freezer salad
directions: Shred cabbage, pepper and carrots; set aside. Boil vinegar, water, sugar, mustard and celery seed. Let cool.
Pour over cabbage. Marinate 24 hours.

title: spoon bread
directions: Add meal, shortening and salt to boiling water; cook 5 minutes and cool.
Add eggs and milk; mix.
Pour into a warm well-greased (put in oven to do this) 1-quart baking dish and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: irish oatmeal cookies
directions: In large bowl or mixer, beat butter and both sugars until creamy.
Add eggs, vanilla, flour, milk and baking soda.
Add oatmeal and raisins.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheets. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.
Makes about 60 cookies.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Pat hamburger into patties.
Place in long baking dish. Top with mushrooms and soup.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook broiler and season with salt.
Bone and chop into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients well.

title: pistachio pudding salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill before serving.

title: chicken mousse
directions: Remove excess fat from the fryer.
Cook in 1 1/2 quarts water with the garlic, bay leaves, celery leaves, parsley and salt. About halfway through cooking, add the white pepper.
When chicken is cooked, remove from broth and cool.
Strain broth and set in refrigerator until fat is congealed on top and can be removed. Remove skin, bones, etc., from chicken meat.
Refrigerate.
This can be done the night before.

title: 1-2-3-4 layer cake
directions: Put the spice batter into two other pans; then bake the four layers.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 to 35 minutes.
When the layers have cooled, put together with the filling and frost with Caramel Frosting.

title: fruit and cream pie
directions: * Use flavor of fruit selected.

title: the cake that won't last
directions: Combine all ingredients by hand until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients except mushrooms and tomato paste. Simmer slowly until meat is in shreds.
Usually takes 3 to 4 hours.
Add the tomato paste and mushrooms about 1/2 hour before serving.
Cook spaghetti in salted water and serve with sauce. Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: bean soup with ham(this is a good soup for a cold day.)
directions: In a large kettle, boil ham, onion, seasonings and beans until tender (about 2 hours).
Keep plenty of water in kettle.
Mash with potato masher and serve hot.
(This soup is good with cornbread.)
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chile cheese dip
directions: Mix chile, green chiles and diced Velveeta cheese in a medium glass mixing bowl; microwave for 3 minutes on High.
In 2-minute intervals, cook and then stir for approximately 8 minutes or until cheese has melted and all ingredients have mixed together.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: ribs and kraut
directions: Season ribs and add onion.
Bake, uncovered, in oven at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Ribs should be nice and brown.
Cover with kraut and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Return to oven and bake for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: shaky salad
directions: Mix jello with hot water.
Add other ingredients; mix well. Chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: chicken breasts with rice
directions: Presoak in salt water the chicken.
Put rice in bottom of long, buttered casserole dish.
Place drained chicken breasts, large side up, on top of rice.
Mix together the soups, soup mix and water. Reserve 1 cup of mixture.
Pour remainder over chicken breasts and bake, covered, at 450° until bubbly.
Turn down and cook at 350° until tender.
Add reserved cup of soup mixture about 10 minutes before it's done.

title: texas pecan pie
directions: Mix syrup, sugar, butter, salt and vanilla; add slightly beaten eggs.
Put in pie crust.
Sprinkle pecans over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat until creamy and smooth.
Pour into crust or graham cracker crust.
Shred chocolate on top.

title: beef and vegetable chowder
directions: Cook hamburger and onion in margarine until browned.
Add water, tomatoes, celery, salt, bouillon cubes, bay leaf, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Bring to boil, cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add vegetables, noodles and thyme.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: creamy lime chiller
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender; process until smooth. Serves 2. Multiply ingredients as needed for more servings.

title: madonna salad
directions: Bring to a boil the first 2 ingredients; remove from heat. Cool.
Beat in the cream cheese and baby food.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: summer icebox pickles
directions: Layer and place uncovered in refrigerator overnight.
Next morning, put in two quart jars.
Keeps in refrigerator 3 months.

title: pat's omelet
directions: Beat eggs and pour onto hot griddle.
Turn once, when done layer next 4 ingredients onto 1 side and fold omelet over.
Enjoy with a slice of toast and good cup of coffee.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix shortening, chocolate and granulated sugar.
Blend in 1 egg at a time, until well mixed.
Add vanilla.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Mix all ingredients (except chocolate kisses) together. Roll into
1-inch
balls.
Bake	at
375° for approximately 8 minutes. After removing from oven, place candy kiss in center of cookie and push down until side of cookie cracks.

title: caponata
directions: Heat oil in large nonstick skillet; add eggplant, mushrooms, onion, garlic, basil, oregano and bell pepper.
Saute 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Blend in diced tomatoes and juice, tomato sauce, seasoned salt and pepper; simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in vinegar, olives and red pepper sauce.
Serve warm or cold in bowl accompanied by bread, crackers or vegetable dippers.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Place sugar and cinnamon in plastic bag.
Add pieces of biscuit, a few at a time, and shake to coat.
Place pieces in greased tube pan until all are coated. Sprinkle layers with nuts and raisins.
Bring brown sugar and butter to a boil in a saucepan.
Pour over top of biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Allow to cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.
Turn top side up to serve.

title: ozark pork roast
directions: Rub 1/2 teaspoon of salt and 1/4 teaspoon of pepper over roast.
Dredge in flour.
Brown roast on all sides in margarine and oil in a large, deep, cast-iron skillet.
Remove roast from skillet; drain on paper towels.
Saute onion in drippings until tender.
Place roast over onions.
Add carrots and potatoes. Sprinkle remaining salt and pepper over vegetables.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until meat is done.
Place vegetables around roast to serve.
Serves 4.

title: cracker treats
directions: Mix all spices with oil.
Put crackers in a brown paper bag. Pour oil in bag; shake until oil is absorbed.

title: snappy cheese wafers
directions: Cut butter into flour until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Mix in cheese, salt and pepper.
Fold in Rice Krispies.
Pinch off small pieces.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet and pat flat. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: cookie jar gingersnaps
directions: Sift flour, ginger, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar (adding sugar gradually).
Add egg and molasses to creamed mixture and beat.
Then add sifted dry ingredients to mixture.
Form teaspoonfuls of dough into small balls and and roll in sugar to cover the outside surface.
Place on ungreased pan, 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until tops are slightly rounded, crackly and light brown. Remove from sheet, cool completely on wire rack and store in airtight container.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: autumn soup
directions: In large saucepan cook and stir meat until brown.
Drain fat. Cook onions with meat until onions are tender, about 5 minutes. Stir in remaining ingredients; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: layered jello salad
directions: Dissolve box of Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Take half of mixture and add 1/2 cup cold water.
Pour into a 2-quart glass dish and refrigerate.
Put 2 heaping tablespoonfuls ice cream in remaining Jell-O.
Add to refrigerated Jell-O when firm.
Repeat these steps with 2 more boxes of Jell-O.
Keep refrigerated.
I start with grape, blackberry or blueberry, then next layer, I use strawberry, raspberry or cherry.
For the third layer, I use orange, apricot or lemon.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells according to directions on box.
Drain and rinse. Mix other ingredients well and stuff into shells.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Heat well; do not boil.
Pour over meatballs.
Cover and bake in oven at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Remove cover and bake 15 minutes longer.
Delicious!

title: baked beans and bacon
directions: In a large frypan, cook cut up bacon 15 minutes. Cook onion and green pepper in bacon drippings 3 to 4 minutes.
Pour off drippings.
Add bacon and remaining ingredients.
Heat, covered, on low heat 1 hour. Remove cover, stir and continue heating, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Mix the cheeses together. Spread half of sour cream mixture in 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 the cheese.
Add remainder of sour cream mix then remainder of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: snowbound hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in a closed quart jar.

title: wild rice rose
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Put in buttered 2-quart casserole. Cover and bake 1 hour.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Bring cream to boil; set aside.
Bring sugar and water to boil.
With a pastry brush dipped in cold water, make a line around the inside of the saucepan just above the boiling mixture. Cook over high heat until mixture is golden brown.
Remove from heat and let cool a bit.
Add cream to mixture.
Bring to boil and cook over low heat 2 to 3 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Makes 3 cups.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Arrange diced turkey in a large greased baking dish.
Melt butter in a large skillet and saute the celery, onion and bread crumbs.
Add salt, baking powder, pepper and poultry seasoning. Beat the egg and add soup and broth (or milk).
Add to crumb mixture and pour over the turkey.
Bake uncovered 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate drop peanut butter cookies
directions: Boil together for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes the margarine, cocoa and milk.
Remove from heat and add other ingredients.
Drop on waxed paper immediately and let set.

title: picadillo cubano
directions: Mix meats with salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 cup sherry.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Saute in oil: garlic, onion, pepper, capers and olives.
Add meat and remaining ingredients.
Cook 1 hour over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining 1/2 cup sherry.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serves 6.
Good over rice.

title: marshmallow cookie pops
directions: Melt chocolate and shortening together in pan.
Put a toothpick into each marshmallow.
Dip marshmallow into chocolate mixture, coating well.
Roll in cookie crumbs or chopped nuts. Yummy!!

title: popovers
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk.
Then add flour and salt.
Beat vigorously for 2 minutes.
Pour batter into very hot greased custard cups or iron popover pans (425°) for about 40 minutes in preheated oven.
Serve at once.
Makes 6 large popovers.

title: hershey chocolate pie
directions: Melt 5 Hershey bars in microwave.
Pour into Cool Whip.
Mix and pour into crust.
Take last chocolate bar and break off squares.
Put on top of pie, leaving 3 squares.
Take last 3 squares and grate on top of pie.
Refrigerate 2 hours and serve.

title: pineapple zucchini loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9 x 5 loaf pans. Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla; blend.
Add zucchini.
Sift dry ingredients; add to batter.
Stir in pineapple, nuts and raisins.
Bake about 1 hour until toothpick comes out clean. Cool before removing from pans.
Wrap and store overnight to develop flavors before slicing.

title: chocolate gravy like granny's
directions: Mix all ingredients into large cooker. Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly so it doesn't stick. Cook until gravy starts to thicken. Takes about 10 minutes.

title: creole style green beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon.
Into remaining bacon fat in pan, add onion and green pepper and cook until tender. Blend in flour, sugar, Worcestershire, salt and pepper and the mustard.
Add the tomatoes.
Cook, stirring unti thickened.
Add the green beans and heat well.
To serve add the beans with the bacon.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked lime chicken
directions: About 1 1/4 hours before serving, preheat oven to 400°. Grate, peel and squeeze 2 tablespoons juice from limes.
Place chicken in bowl.
Toss with lime juice.

title: provencial salad(horiatiki salata)
directions: Rub
clove
of	garlic	around	sides
of
bowl.
Place tomatoes, onions and cucumbers in bowl.
Very gently toss with olive oil and vinegar to which the seasonings have been added. Add Feta cheese and anchovies (optional) and serve.

title: the david's chili chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Simmer 45 minutes until chicken is tender.
Refrigerate chicken and broth.
Debone and chop chicken.
Reserve 1/2 cup of broth.
Combine chicken, broth, tortillas, soups, milk, sour cream, onions and chilies. Place in a 9 x 13-inch or larger baking dish.
Top with cheese and cover tightly with foil.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour covered.
Remove foil and bake an additional 10 minutes. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: seven-layer salad
directions: Layer all ingredients in order listed in a large salad bowl. Chill covered for at least 8 hours. Toss before serving.
Yields 12 servings.

title: southern fried catfish
directions: Cut fish into serving-size pieces if fillets are large. Combine cornmeal, flour, salt and pepper.
Coat fish with cornmeal mixture.
Heat oil (1/2-inch) in skillet until hot.
Fry fish in hot oil, turning carefully, until brown on both sides, about 10 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: not just your everyday banana cake!(kass's favorite)
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients with electric mixer until moistened. Then add the eggs and the second 1/3 cup of buttermilk.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: brunch champagne punch
directions: Combine the champagne and juice in a punch bowl.
Add orange slices to float in the bowl.
Serves 20.

title: plantation frost
directions: In a blender (or with an electric mixer) blend coffee, sugar and banana until smooth.
Add ice cream and blend until smooth. Makes 3 cups.

title: fat free french dressing
directions: Blend together and let stand 30 minutes.
Contains 5 calories per tablespoon.

title: chocolate peanut clusters(for microwave oven)
directions: In medium glass bowl, heat chocolate at Medium-low 3 to 4 minutes, or until chocolate is melted; stir in milk until smooth, then peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased waxed paper lined cookie sheet; chill until set.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve
yeast in warm water.	Mix dry ingredients and cut in shortening
or
you
can
put shortening into milk and microwave for
1 minute.
Let cool; add yeast mixture to milk; work into flour.
Roll
out
on
floured
board
and	cut out (biscuits do not have to rise).	Bake for 15 minutes at 400°. I use RapidRise yeast
(Fleischmann's).
It
works better for me.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Mix sugar and butter until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, mix after each one.
Add all dry ingredients and mix well.
Add milk, vanilla, orange peel, nuts and zucchini; mix well.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.

title: krummel kuchen(crumb cake)
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; cut or work in shortening. Reserve 1 cup of mixture.
To remaining mixture, add combined eggs and milk.
Beat well.
Pour into greased 9-inch coffee cake pan. Cover top with reserved mixture.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nut meats.
Bake in a moderate oven (350° to 374°) for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese potatoes supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour or more at 375°.

title: crab eggplant casserole
directions: Boil eggplant in water about 25 minutes; drain and mash. Combine eggplant, onion, bell pepper, 1 cup bread crumbs, 1 1/2 cups grated cheese, salt, pepper and margarine.
Mix well.
Add crabmeat and beaten eggs.
Mix and pour in buttered 2-quart casserole.
Spread remaining cheese and bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Beat eggs in separate bowl.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked herbed fish
directions: Place fish in a greased baking pan. Combine remaining ingredients and spoon evenly over fish. Bake in preheated 350° oven 10 to 15 minutes until fish is opaque and flakes easily with a fork; do not overcook. Makes 4 servings.

title: sunshine carrots
directions: Bias-slice carrots crosswise about 1/2-inch thick.
Place in saucepan containing 1-inch of boiling salted water.
Cover and cook 10 to 20 minutes or just until carrots are tender.
Drain.

title: baked potatoes (stuffed)
directions: Bake potatoes on center rack of 450° preheated oven until soft.
Cut thin slice lengthwise from top of each potato.
Scoop out flesh; keep shell.
Throw away top of each potato.
Mash flesh with mixer and add sour cream and salt.
Mix until fluffy.
(Add a little milk, if you prefer it thinner).
Add cheese and mix.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Mix butter, nuts and flour.
Press into a 9 x 9-inch dish. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Put on top of first layer.
Beat instant pudding and milk until thick.
Spread on top of second layer.
Spread rest of Cool Whip on top.
Can top with grated chocolate if desired.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and margarine.
Pat into a pie pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and softened cream cheese until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Pour over crumb crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool, then cover with pie filling.
Chill several hours.
(We usually double this recipe and use a 9-inch pie pan.)

title: summer pasta
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil over low heat, but don't let it brown.
Add tomatoes.
Cook, stirring frequently.
Meanwhile, cook pasta al dente; drain.
Mix pasta, tomato mixture, Romano cheese, Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella cheese, mixing well.
Add basil and serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hot mexican dip
directions: Cook and stir beef and onions in a 10-inch skillet until brown; drain.
Stir in taco sauce, beans and 1 cup of the cheese. Heat, stirring occasionally until cheese is melted.
Pour into serving dish and sprinkle remaining cheese on top in a ring. Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: frances kennedy's rolls
directions: Heat to melt 1/2 cup water, Crisco, sugar and salt.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
When both mixtures are cool, add together.
Add beaten egg and add sifted flour.
Put in refrigerator
6 hours or overnight.
Make out in pan; cover with cloth.
Let rise 2 hours.
Bake in hot oven, 400°, for 12 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt.
In mixer bowl, beat butter and shortening about 30 seconds.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Add dry ingredients, beating until well blended; stir in chocolate pieces and nuts.
Drop from a teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 8 to 10 minutes or until browned around edges.
Remove from oven; let stand on cookie sheet for
2 minutes.
Do not stack until completely cool.

title: egg nog bread(taste of home, december 1994)
directions: In large bowl, combine butter, sugar and eggs; beat well. Stir in flour, baking powder and salt alternately with egg nog. Fold in nuts, raisins and cherries. Bake in 350° oven for 70 minutes in greased 9 x 5 loaf pan.

title: jalapeno popcorn
directions: Chop and slice peppers. Place in oil or butter in bottom of popcorn popper. Place kernels in. Pop corn.

title: cheesabutter
directions: Beat together butter with Italian seasoning.
Add garlic powder and black pepper.
Blend in cheese and lemon juice.
Form into log shape on wax paper and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: kendallville joes
directions: Brown meat and onions in skillet.
Stir in ketchup.
Mix and let simmer together for about 15 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Some water can be added if you want.
Serve on toasted bun.

title: bob boyardee's famous italian spaghetti sauce(slow cooker recipe)
directions: Combine meats and brown together.
Drain well.
Combine with all ingredients, except optional stewed tomatoes, in 5-quart slow cooker.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or on high for 3 to 4 hours.
Add tomatoes during last hour of cooking time.
Serve over noodles with garlic bread on the side.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: old fashion cream pie
directions: Mix together and put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 15 minutes at 425°, then for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: quick pizza dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat cream cheese and seasonings with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Spread on bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Top with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, pizza sauce, remaining 1 cup Mozzarella and peppers.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until mixture is thoroughly heated and cheese is melted.
Serve with breadsticks.

title: play beads(not edible, but lots of fun!)
directions: You will also need felt-tip markers, colorless nail polish and cord for stringing.

title: broccoli and chicken makeover
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Layer rice and broccoli, then chicken in a shallow 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine soup and curry; spread mixture evenly over chicken.
Top with cheese and bake 35 to 45 minutes, until casserole bubbles and cheese melts.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, flour, soda and salt together. Then add eggs, spice, nuts and apples.
Bake in 7 x 11-inch greased and floured pan at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: caramel chex mix
directions: In 1 1/2-quart saucepan, melt oleo and stir in sugar, syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil; keep stirring.
Boil 5 minutes, without stirring.
Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Pour over cereal mixture and mix well until evenly coated.

title: sue cobb's punch recipe
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Before serving, add 2 quarts of ginger ale and pour over crushed ice.

title: wine sauce for baked chicken breast
directions: Make roux from this:
margarine, chicken fat and flour.
Add cayenne pepper and salt.
Mix chicken broth.
Enhance broth with bouillon cubes and milk.
Cook with roux until thickened.
Mix wine into other mixture and stir well.
Pour over cooked chicken breast that has been placed over cooked rice.
Bake until hot.
Serve.

title: pizza squash
directions: Saute small onion in butter. Add tomato sauce. Heat and boil 1 minute. Pour sauce over squash. Shake oregano over all. Top with lots of mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 30-45 minutes or until squash is tender.

title: fruit drops
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well.
Stir in milk.
Sift flour, soda and salt together and add.
Stir in the rest of ingredients. Chill for at least an hour.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes (until almost no imprint is seen when touched lightly).
Makes 8 dozen.
Mellows with age.

title: country company potatoes
directions: Heat 1/4 cup butter and chicken soup; mix in cheese, onion, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Stir until barely mixed with potatoes.
Pour out in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat down level and top with corn flakes and 2 tablespoons butter (slice and dot over the corn flakes).
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Heat oil in heavy large skillet over medium heat.
Add onion; saute until tender, about 10 minutes.
Add garlic; saute 1 minute. Add mushrooms and crushed red pepper; saute until mushrooms just begin to soften, about 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes (cut up) and reserved juices.
Cover and cook around 2 hours on low heat. Makes enough sauce for 1 package spaghetti.
Makes 6 servings.

title: "best ever" coconut fruit cake
directions: Save 4 pieces of pineapple, 6 red and 6 green cherries and 1 dozen pecan halves to garnish top.
Chop rest of fruit and pecans. Grate coconut and add dates.
Add the coconut milk to the fruit. Refrigerate overnight.
Next day put fruit in large pan and mix well.
Add sugar, well beaten eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder and combine thoroughly with fruit mixture. Grease tube pan with shortening and line with 2 layers of brown paper cut to fit bottom of pan.
Grease paper lining and flour lightly.
Pour mixture into pan; garnish and bake at 300° for 15 minutes, then at 325° for 1 hour or longer.
Test with straw for doneness.
Let cool 20 minutes, then peel off paper and place on wire rack until completely cooled.
Pour 1/2 cup of apricot brandy over cake and wrap well in foil.
Every so often pour 1/2 cup brandy over the cake and keep in airtight container in cool place until ripened.
Bake last of November in order for it to be ripe at Christmas.
This cake is delicious.

title: creamy scalloped potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Remove from hot water, drain and cool slightly.
Peel potatoes and slice very thin.
Set aside. Combine sour cream, cheese, onion, milk, salt and pepper.
Mix potatoes with sauce mixture.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch glass casserole dish, sprayed with nonfat cooking spray.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, or until bubbly.
Serves 12.
Each serving contains 149 calories and 0.2 fat grams.

title: linguine with clam sauce
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, saute garlic in hot oil.
Add onion and saute until soft.
Do not brown. Add wine and chicken broth, then clams with liquid.
Add seafood (if desired) and pepper, Tabasco and oregano. Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together in large salad bowl (sprinkle bananas with lemon juice unless eaten promptly).

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt Milky Way in double boiler. Cream oleo and sugar. Add 1 egg at a time, mix well. Sift flour and pinch of salt. Add soda to buttermilk. Add flour and buttermilk alternately to butter, eggs and sugar mix. Add Milky Way bars and beat well. Add vanilla, pecans and bake in greased and floured pan in 300°
oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: shrimp and vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place green beans, corn and shrimp in a single layer on a 12 x 18-inch sheet of aluminum foil.
Top with snow peas, margarine, water and lemon juice.
Sprinkle with parsley, salt and pepper to taste.
Wrap in foil.
Place foil on cookie sheet.
Cook 16 minutes.

title: "harker" broccoli soup
directions: Cook potatoes, onion, celery and broccoli until all are tender.
Do not drain water.
Add cream of mushroom soup, then fill both empty soup cans with milk and add to soup as well.
Stir and add Velveeta cheese.
Heat, but do not boil.

title: great chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: brownie oat cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
In another bowl mix liquids.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Bake on nonstick cookie sheets at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: prune bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix moist ingredients together.
Flour and grease tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Can bake in mini loaf pans, approximately 20 to 25 minutes.

title: raisin molasses cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and beaten egg.
Sift together and add flour, cinnamon, ginger and soda.
Cook together boiling water and raisins.
Add to mixture.
Drop by teaspoon.
Bake for 10 minutes in 375° oven.
Frost them with a plain powdered sugar frosting when cool, if you wish.

title: lemon chicken with thyme
directions: In a plastic or paper bag, combine the flour, salt and pepper and shake to mix.
Add the chicken and shake to coat lightly. Remove the chicken and reserve the excess seasoned flour.

title: yummy punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except ginger ale and sherbet.
Pour over ice.
Add ginger ale and sherbet just before serving.
Makes 12 to 15 cups.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg.
Mix.
Add buttermilk.
Set aside.
Add salt, soda and baking powder to flour and sift.
Add to other mixture.
Beat.
Add nuts, dates and cherries.
Chill about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: marshmallow cream fudge
directions: In medium saucepan, mix cream, butter, salt, milk and sugar. Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly (before and during boiling).
Take off heat.
Stir in chips until melted thoroughly.
Add vanilla.
Pour into 8-inch greased pan. Chill until firm.

title: creole limas
directions: Cook limas as directed.
Saute celery, onion, pepper and garlic in some of bacon drippings.
Mix all in casserole; bake 1 hour at 350°.
Top with bacon.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix all the ingredients and chill thoroughly.
Taste, and if not sweet enough, add sugar. But the fruit cocktail should make it sweet enough.

title: tomato casserole
directions: Oil the bottom of a pan with olive oil.
Put a single layer of sliced tomatoes, then onions and then tomatoes.
Sprinkle on cheese, Season-All, salt, red pepper and seasoned bread crumbs. Put bread crumbs on heavy.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: banquet beans
directions: Fry onion and bacon until onion is transparent.
Add ketchup, brown sugar, vinegar and mustard; cook for 3 minutes.
Pour into casserole dish.
Add beans and kielbasa; mix together.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken and stuffing bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions. Spoon stuffing across center of 2-quart shallow baking pan. Arrange 3 chicken pieces on each side of stuffing, overlapping if necessary. Combine soup, milk and parsley. Pour over chicken. Cover with foil. Bake 15 minutes. Uncover and bake 10 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.

title: shrimp creole
directions: The most difficult meal for an average housewife to get is dinner out.

title: stuffed grapevine leaves with avgolemono sauce
directions: Combine meat, onions, rice, salt and pepper. Add water and mix well.

Drain brine from jar of grapevine leaves, then place in large bowl and wash well with clear water to remove all traces of brine. Cover bottom of greased casserole dish with torn leaves. Fold some of the meat mixture in the center of a leaf and roll leaf tightly.
Repeat until all mixture is rolled in leaves. Arrange rolls in layers. Dissolve bouillon cubes in enough water to cover rolls.
Pour bouillon over all and dot with butter.
Put a heavy plate on top to keep rolls from opening.
Cover casserole and cook over low heat for at least 2 hours.

title: standard roll recipe
directions: If a greater amount of sugar is used, the rolls will be sweeter.
If a greater amount of shortening is used, the rolls will be richer and more tender.

Not less than 2 or more than 8 tablespoons of sugar or shortening should be used, however, follow general directions for making bread, kneading in a little less flour and permitting the dough to become lighter during each rising process, both after it is shaped and before the rolls are placed in the oven.

title: christmas coconut balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into balls. Chill 30 minutes. Dip in melted chocolate.
Place on waxed paper.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt 1 stick butter in baking dish.
Mix batter together and pour
in baking dish.
Pour 1 large can peaches on batter. Sprinkle with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all together and bake in casserole at 375° for 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: hershey's chocolate cake
directions: Cream the margarine.
Add the sugar.
Add the eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Sift the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add the chocolate syrup and vanilla with flour mixture.
Bake in sheet pan at 350° for 30 or 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Frost.

title: karen's cheese biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl, cut shortening into flour with fork or pastry blender until consistency of coarse meal.
Add milk; stir with fork until mixture leaves sides of bowl and forms a soft, moist dough.
One to three tablespoons additional milk may be added to achieve desired consistency.
Turn onto floured surface.
Knead gently 6 to 10 times or until no longer sticky.
Cut block of cheese into chunks.
Pinch dough off into 1/4 size of a baseball. Put a chunk of cheese in the center and proceed to roll into a ball.
Press knuckles gently on top and position biscuits on ungreased pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put all ingredients in an ungreased casserole dish.
Do not stir or mix.
Bake 1/2 hour.
Take out and stir.
Bake for another 1/2 hour.
Then done.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O in hot water; stir well.
Add 2 cups cold water. Let chill until thickened some.
Add pineapple (drained; save juice).
Add sliced bananas to Jell-O.
Add miniature marshmallows.
Let set until firm.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt butter and cocoa together.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar and beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour, salt, coconut, chopped nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
While still hot, spread marshmallow cream on top.

title: fish batter
directions: With wire whisk in medium bowl, combine beer or club soda, lemon juice, egg, Bisquick and flour.
When smooth, let stand 10 minutes.
Moisten and lightly flour fish fillets.
Let dry a few minutes.
Dip to coat in wet batter.
Do not use tongs.
Use tip of sharp knife to spear fillets.
Drop batter coated fillets into 385° oil, a few at a time, frying a few minutes on each side, until golden and crispy.
Serves 4.

title: tomato casserole
directions: Mix tomatoes, bread and crackers together.
Smooth down top. Lay small pieces of butter over top, then cheese and bacon.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes.

title: kielbasi fondue
directions: Put all ingredients, except kielbasi, in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add sliced kielbasi; simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: beef paprika(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Add onions and garlic and cook until onions are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients including 1 1/2 cups water.
Cover and simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
(If using tenderloin tips, cook for 1 hour.)

title: nacho dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of pie pan.
Spread chili on top.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Microwave 7 minutes.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Store in an airtight container.
To serve, add 1/4 cup mix to 8 ounces hot water.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat; brown green pepper and add onion flakes.
Add soup and beans.
Add pinch of oregano and tablespoon of sugar.
Add tablespoon of chili powder.
Add parsley and black pepper.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix all ingredients into punch bowl.
Let sherbet float on top.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: Place eggs, sugar, butter, flour, cocoa, vanilla and salt in small mixer bowl.
Beat 4 minutes.
Stir in nuts and pour into greased 8-inch pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until done. Pie will settle a meringue when cool.
Cut in wedges and serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
Serves 8.

title: piquant cocktail meat balls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine beef, cornflake crumbs, parsley flakes, eggs, soy sauce, pepper, garlic powder, catsup and minced onion.
Blend.
Form mixture in small meat balls, about the size of walnuts.
Arrange meatballs in a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.

title: nut pound cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt, mace and set aside.
Cream butter and sugar in large bowl.
Beat to fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla, stir in nuts.
Pour in greased and floured large tube pan or three (9-inch) pans.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 or 50 minutes.
Cool and turn on rack to finish cooling.
Ice with Caramel Icing.

title: chicken a la orange
directions: Preheat oven to 375°F.
Rinse chicken and pat dry with paper towels.
Mix together orange juice, soy sauce and ginger.
Place in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil and then lower the heat and simmer for 5 minutes or until thickened.
Watch carefully so that it does not evaporate too much.
Brush the chicken breasts with the glaze and place in an ovenproof dish.
Bake uncovered for 25 minutes, basting occasionally.
Garnish with orange slices.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion.
When done, add mushroom soup.
Then place half of mixture into casserole dish.
Mix the rest with herb dressing and place on the rest of the mixture.
May top with sliced Cheddar cheese.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Grease and flour Bundt pan or 2 bread pans.
Pour mixture in pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cream puff dough
directions: Bring water and butter to a boil.
Add flour; mix well.
Add eggs, 1 at a time; dough will be stiff.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
When cool, fill with pudding, salad spreads, etc.

title: caramel candy bar cookies
directions: For cookie crust, combine flour, oats and baking soda.
In a mixing bowl, beat margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in oat mixture until crumbly.
Don't overmix.
Reserve 1 cup of this crust mixture.
Press remainder into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.

title: pork chop-apple bake
directions: Brown pork chops lightly in cooking oil. Slice and core apples 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick. Arrange pork chops in long baking dish. Arrange layer of apples on top.
Sprinkle with brown sugar. Add water. Cover with foil. Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: dijon chicken roll-ups
directions: Spread chicken with Dijon mustard.
Place 2 slices of cheese on each breast.
Roll up and secure with toothpicks.
Place chicken into microwave-safe baking dish.
Melt margarine 30 seconds in glass measuring cup and pour over chicken.
Shake bread crumbs over chicken and cook on High 8 to 10 minutes, covered. Turn chicken rolls over and rearrange once.
Allow to stand covered for 5 minutes before serving.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt Milky Way bars and 1 stick oleo; set aside.
Cream sugar and 1 stick oleo; add eggs.
Add flour and soda alternately with buttermilk.
Add melted candy and oleo mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.

title: curried-coconut shrimp
directions: Cook 1 pound shelled shrimp; drain.
In saucepan melt 1/4 cup butter or margarine.
Stir in 3 tablespoons all-purpose flour.
Add 1 1/2 cups milk all at once; cook and stir till thickened and bubbly.
Add shrimp, 1/4 cup dry sherry, 1/2 teaspoon salt, dash pepper, and dash paprika.
Pour into 5 coquilles (individual baking shells).
Sprinkle each serving with 1 tablespoon grated Parmesan cheese.
Broil 3 to 4 inches from heat till cheese browns.
Makes 5 servings.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease tube pan.
Cream butter in large bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Gradually add sugar, creaming until light and fluffy.
By hand, stir in flour, dry frosting mix and walnuts until well blended.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: walking tacos
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish, layer the bean dip, avocados, taco mix with the mayonnaise and sour cream stirred into it, cheese, onions, tomatoes and olives.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: sticky buns
directions: Thaw dough according to package directions.
Distribute nuts evenly in bottom of a greased Bundt or angel food pan.
Roll thawed balls in cinnamon (if desired).
Put balls on top of the nuts.
Sprinkle with pudding mix.
Melt butter and brown sugar. Pour over dough.
Cover with plastic wrap; let dough rise until double in size.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Turn upside down on dish; cool.

title: puff 'n' stuff balls
directions: Combine crab with minced vegetables, 1/2 teaspoon pepper and 1/4 teaspoon paprika. Shape into small balls.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: crazy wacky cake
directions: Mix first five ingredients in an ungreased oblong glass baking dish.
Make three holes, a large one, medium one and small one. Pour oil in large hole, vinegar in medium hole and vanilla in small hole.
Pour water over all.
Mix with fork.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix water and milk; stir into dry ingredients.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot grease in a deep pan.
Fry for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients; put in lightly greased dish.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Grate Cheddar cheese; chop onion and jalapeno peppers; brown beef and drain well.
Mix and set aside: cornmeal, eggs, corn, milk, bacon drippings (very essential for flavor), salt and soda. Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease bottom of cast-iron skillet; cover bottom with corn meal and brown slightly on top of stove.
Pour 1/2 batter into skillet; layer cheese, meat, onions and peppers. Cover with remaining batter and bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Saute ground beef, onion, bell pepper, salt and pepper.
Mix cornbread, corn and egg.
Put half of cornbread-corn mixture in square Pyrex dish.
Put meat mixture on top of this.
Top with chopped jalapeno peppers.
Top with cheese.
Add rest of cornbread mix.
Cook at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: simple salisbury steak
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/4 cup of the soup, beef, bread crumbs, egg and onion.
Shape into 6 patties.
Cook patties over medium-high heat in skillet until browned.
Remove.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in remaining soup and mushrooms.
Return patties to skillet.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 20 minutes or until done, turning occasionally.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: breakfast drink
directions: Place all in blender and blend until smooth.

title: hush puppies
directions: Heat oil to 375°.
Mix corn meal, flour, baking powder, sugar, onion, milk, egg, and salt.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil a few at a time, or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: easy chile verde
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook in crock-pot for 8 hours on low or 3 hours on high.
If gravy is too thin, can be thickened with cornstarch and water.
Serve with flour tortillas and cheese.

title: meatballs and onion gravy
directions: Place ground chuck in a bowl, season with TexJoy steak seasoning. Crush crackers finely and add to meat; mix. Add onion and egg. Mix well and form into small balls. Drop into medium hot skillet, that has been sprayed with Pam, and brown lightly on all sides, taking care not to stir the meatballs too much, or they will fall apart. If there is excessive grease, drain. (A small amount left in skillet adds to the flavor.)

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; add eggs, oil, zucchini and nuts. Mix until blended.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: my own southern style buttermilk cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease well a 10-inch iron skillet or 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mix together cornmeal, baking powder, baking soda, salt and sugar until well combined.
In separate bowl, mix together buttermilk, beaten eggs and drippings (or butter).
